var book = {
	"name": "Leviticus",
	"numChapters": 27,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2747A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2747A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to Moses and spoke to him from the tent of meeting, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘When any man of you brings an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2748B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2748B\"></sup>offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall bring your offering of animals from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2748C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2748C\"></sup>the herd or the flock.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If his offering is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2749D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2749D\"></sup>burnt offering from the herd, he shall offer it, a male <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2749E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2749E\"></sup>without defect; he shall offer it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2749F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2749F\"></sup>at the doorway of the tent of meeting, that he may be accepted before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2750G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2750G\"></sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of the burnt offering, that it may be accepted for him to make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2750H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2750H\"></sup>atonement on his behalf.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2751I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2751I\"></sup>He shall slay the young bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and Aaron’s sons the priests shall offer up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2751J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2751J\"></sup>the blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2751K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2751K\"></sup>sprinkle the blood around on the altar that is at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2752L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2752L\"></sup>He shall then skin the burnt offering and cut it into its pieces.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2753M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2753M\"></sup>The sons of Aaron the priest shall put fire on the altar and arrange wood on the fire.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Aaron’s sons the priests shall arrange the pieces, the head and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2754N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2754N\"></sup>suet over the wood which is on the fire that is on the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2755O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2755O\"></sup>entrails, however, and its legs he shall wash with water. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2755P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2755P\"></sup>the priest shall offer up in smoke all of it on the altar for a burnt offering, an offering by fire of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2755Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2755Q\"></sup>a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘But if his offering is from the flock, of the sheep or of the goats, for a burnt offering, he shall offer it a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2756R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2756R\"></sup>male without defect.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2757S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2757S\"></sup>He shall slay it on the side of the altar northward before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Aaron’s sons the priests shall sprinkle its blood around on the altar.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall then cut it into its pieces with its head and its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2758T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2758T\"></sup>suet, and the priest shall arrange them on the wood which is on the fire that is on the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The entrails, however, and the legs he shall wash with water. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2759U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2759U\"></sup>the priest shall offer all of it, and offer it up in smoke on the altar; it is a burnt offering, an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘But if his offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a burnt offering of birds, then he shall bring his offering from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2760V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2760V\"></sup>turtledoves or from young pigeons.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest shall bring it to the altar, and wring off its head and offer it up in smoke on the altar; and its blood is to be drained out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2761W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2761W\"></sup>on the side of the altar.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He shall also take away its crop with its feathers and cast it beside the altar eastward, to the place of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2762X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2762X\"></sup>ashes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he shall tear it by its wings, <i>but</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2763Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2763Y\"></sup>shall not sever <i>it</i>. And the priest shall offer it up in smoke on the altar on the wood which is on the fire; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2763Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2763Z\"></sup>it is a burnt offering, an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>‘Now when anyone presents a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2764A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2764A\"></sup>grain offering as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, his offering shall be of fine flour, and he shall pour oil on it and put frankincense on it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He shall then bring it to Aaron’s sons the priests; and shall take from it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2765B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2765B\"></sup>his handful of its fine flour and of its oil with all of its frankincense. And the priest shall offer <i>it</i> up in smoke <i>as</i> its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2765C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2765C\"></sup>memorial portion on the altar, an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2766D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2766D\"></sup>The remainder of the grain offering belongs to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2766E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2766E\"></sup>Aaron and his sons: a thing most holy, of the offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by fire.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘Now when you bring an offering of a grain offering baked in an oven, <i>it shall be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2767F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2767F\"></sup>unleavened cakes of fine flour mixed with oil, or unleavened wafers spread with oil.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If your offering is a grain offering <i>made</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2768G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2768G\"></sup>on the griddle, <i>it shall be</i> of fine flour, unleavened, mixed with oil;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>you shall break it into bits and pour oil on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now if your offering is a grain offering <i>made</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2770H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2770H\"></sup>in a pan, it shall be made of fine flour with oil.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When you bring in the grain offering which is made of these things to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, it shall be presented to the priest and he shall bring it to the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The priest then shall take up from the grain offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2772I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2772I\"></sup>its memorial portion, and shall offer <i>it</i> up in smoke on the altar <i>as</i> an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2773J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2773J\"></sup>The remainder of the grain offering belongs to Aaron and his sons: a thing most holy of the offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by fire.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2774K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2774K\"></sup>No grain offering, which you bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shall be made with leaven, for you shall not offer up in smoke any leaven or any honey as an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2774L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2774L\"></sup>offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2775M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2775M\"></sup>As an offering of first fruits you shall bring them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but they shall not ascend for a soothing aroma on the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Every grain offering of yours, moreover, you shall season with salt, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2776N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2776N\"></sup>the salt of the covenant of your God shall not be lacking from your grain offering; with all your offerings you shall offer salt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘Also if you bring a grain offering of early ripened things to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2777O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2777O\"></sup>fresh heads of grain roasted in the fire, grits of new growth, for the grain offering of your early ripened things.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You shall then put oil on it and lay incense on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priest shall offer up in smoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2779P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2779P\"></sup>its memorial portion, part of its grits and its oil with all its incense as an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>‘Now if his offering is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2780A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2780A\"></sup>sacrifice of peace offerings, if he is going to offer out of the herd, whether male or female, he shall offer it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2780B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2780B\"></sup>without defect before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2781C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2781C\"></sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of his offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2781D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2781D\"></sup>slay it at the doorway of the tent of meeting, and Aaron’s sons the priests shall sprinkle the blood around on the altar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>From the sacrifice of the peace offerings he shall present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, which is on the loins, and the lobe of the liver, which he shall remove with the kidneys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2784E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2784E\"></sup>Aaron’s sons shall offer <i>it</i> up in smoke on the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2784F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2784F\"></sup>on the burnt offering, which is on the wood that is on the fire; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2784G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2784G\"></sup>it is an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if his offering for a sacrifice of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is from the flock, he shall offer it, male or female, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2785H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2785H\"></sup>without defect.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If he is going to offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2786I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2786I\"></sup>a lamb for his offering, then he shall offer it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2786J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2786J\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2787K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2787K\"></sup>he shall lay his hand on the head of his offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2787L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2787L\"></sup>slay it before the tent of meeting, and Aaron’s sons shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2787M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2787M\"></sup>sprinkle its blood around on the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>From the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2788N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2788N\"></sup>sacrifice of peace offerings he shall bring as an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, its fat, the entire fat tail which he shall remove close to the backbone, and the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, which is on the loins, and the lobe of the liver, which he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2789O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2789O\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the priest shall offer <i>it</i> up in smoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2790P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2790P\"></sup>on the altar <i>as</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2790Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2790Q\"></sup>food, an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>‘Moreover, if his offering is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2791R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2791R\"></sup>a goat, then he shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and he shall lay his hand on its head and slay it before the tent of meeting, and the sons of Aaron shall sprinkle its blood around on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From it he shall present his offering as an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the fat that covers the entrails and all the fat that is on the entrails,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, which is on the loins, and the lobe of the liver, which he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2794S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2794S\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priest shall offer them up in smoke on the altar <i>as</i> food, an offering by fire for a soothing aroma; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2795T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2795T\"></sup>all fat is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2796U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2796U\"></sup>perpetual statute throughout your generations in all your dwellings: you shall not eat any fat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2796V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2796V\"></sup>or any blood.’”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘If a person sins <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2798A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2798A\"></sup>unintentionally in any of the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2798B\"></sup>commanded not to be done, and commits any of them,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2799C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2799C\"></sup>if the anointed priest sins so as to bring guilt on the people, then let him offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a bull without defect as a sin offering for the sin he has committed.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall bring the bull to the doorway of the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2800D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2800D\"></sup>he shall lay his hand on the head of the bull and slay the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2801E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2801E\"></sup>anointed priest is to take some of the blood of the bull and bring it to the tent of meeting,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the priest shall dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle some of the blood seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in front of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2802F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2802F\"></sup>the veil of the sanctuary.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The priest shall also put some of the blood on the horns of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2803G\"></sup>the altar of fragrant incense which is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the tent of meeting; and all the blood of the bull he shall pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering which is at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2804H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2804H\"></sup>He shall remove from it all the fat of the bull of the sin offering: the fat that covers the entrails, and all the fat which is on the entrails,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, which is on the loins, and the lobe of the liver, which he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2805I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2805I\"></sup>with the kidneys",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(just as it is removed from the ox of the sacrifice of peace offerings), and the priest is to offer them up in smoke on the altar of burnt offering.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2807J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2807J\"></sup>the hide of the bull and all its flesh with its head and its legs and its entrails and its refuse,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>that is, all <i>the rest of</i> the bull, he is to bring out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2808K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2808K\"></sup>a clean place outside the camp where the ashes are poured out, and burn it on wood with fire; where the ashes are poured out it shall be burned.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2809L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2809L\"></sup>Now if the whole congregation of Israel commits error and the matter escapes the notice of the assembly, and they commit any of the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded not to be done, and they become guilty;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2810M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2810M\"></sup>when the sin which they have committed becomes known, then the assembly shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2810N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2810N\"></sup>a bull of the herd for a sin offering and bring it before the tent of meeting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2811O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2811O\"></sup>the elders of the congregation shall lay their hands on the head of the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the bull shall be slain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2811P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2811P\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the anointed priest is to bring some of the blood of the bull to the tent of meeting;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2813Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2813Q\"></sup>the priest shall dip his finger in the blood and sprinkle <i>it</i> seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in front of the veil.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He shall put some of the blood on the horns of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2814R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2814R\"></sup>the altar which is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the tent of meeting; and all the blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering which is at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2815S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2815S\"></sup>He shall remove all its fat from it and offer it up in smoke on the altar.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He shall also do with the bull just as he did with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2816T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2816T\"></sup>the bull of the sin offering; thus he shall do with it. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2816U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2816U\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for them, and they will be forgiven.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he is to bring out the bull to <i>a place</i> outside the camp and burn it as he burned the first bull; it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2817V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2817V\"></sup>the sin offering for the assembly.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>‘When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2818W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2818W\"></sup>a leader <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2818X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2818X\"></sup>sins and unintentionally does any one of all the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God has commanded not to be done, and he becomes guilty,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2819Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2819Y\"></sup>if his sin which he has committed is made known to him, he shall bring for his offering a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2819Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2819Z\"></sup>goat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2819AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2819AA\"></sup>a male without defect.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of the male goat and slay it in the place where they slay the burnt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is a sin offering.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the priest is to take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2821AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2821AB\"></sup>the horns of the altar of burnt offering; and <i>the rest of</i> its blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar of burnt offering.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2822AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2822AC\"></sup>All its fat he shall offer up in smoke on the altar as <i>in the case of</i> the fat of the sacrifice of peace offerings. Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2822AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2822AD\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him in regard to his sin, and he will be forgiven.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘Now if anyone of the common people sins <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2823AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2823AE\"></sup>unintentionally in doing any of the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded not to be done, and becomes guilty,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2824AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2824AF\"></sup>if his sin which he has committed is made known to him, then he shall bring for his offering a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2824AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2824AG\"></sup>goat, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2824AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2824AH\"></sup>female without defect, for his sin which he has committed.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2825AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2825AI\"></sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2825AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2825AJ\"></sup>slay the sin offering at the place of the burnt offering.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The priest shall take some of its blood with his finger and put it on the horns of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2826AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2826AK\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2826AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2826AL\"></sup>all <i>the rest of</i> its blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2827AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2827AM\"></sup>Then he shall remove all its fat, just as the fat was removed from the sacrifice of peace offerings; and the priest shall offer it up in smoke on the altar for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2827AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2827AN\"></sup>a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Thus the priest shall make atonement for him, and he will be forgiven.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>‘But if he brings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2828AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2828AO\"></sup>a lamb as his offering for a sin offering, he shall bring it, a female without defect.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2829AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2829AP\"></sup>He shall lay his hand on the head of the sin offering and slay it for a sin offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2829AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2829AQ\"></sup>in the place where they slay the burnt offering.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The priest is to take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horns of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2830AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2830AR\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2830AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2830AS\"></sup>all <i>the rest of</i> its blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2831AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2831AT\"></sup>all its fat, just as the fat of the lamb is removed from the sacrifice of the peace offerings, and the priest shall offer them up in smoke on the altar, on the offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2831AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2831AU\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him in regard to his sin which he has committed, and he will be forgiven."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>‘Now if a person sins after he hears a public <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2832A\"></sup>adjuration <i>to testify</i> when he is a witness, whether he has seen or <i>otherwise</i> known, if he does not tell <i>it</i>, then he will bear his guilt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Or if a person touches <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2833B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2833B\"></sup>any unclean thing, whether a carcass of an unclean beast or the carcass of unclean cattle or a carcass of unclean swarming things, though it is hidden from him and he is unclean, then he will be guilty.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Or if he touches human uncleanness, of whatever <i>sort</i> his uncleanness <i>may</i> be with which he becomes unclean, and it is hidden from him, and then he comes to know <i>it</i>, he will be guilty.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Or if a person <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2835C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2835C\"></sup>swears thoughtlessly with his lips to do evil or to do good, in whatever matter a man may speak thoughtlessly with an oath, and it is hidden from him, and then he comes to know <i>it</i>, he will be guilty in one of these.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So it shall be when he becomes guilty in one of these, that he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2836D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2836D\"></sup>confess that in which he has sinned.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He shall also bring his guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his sin which he has committed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2837E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2837E\"></sup>a female from the flock, a lamb or a goat as a sin offering. So the priest shall make atonement on his behalf for his sin.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘But if he cannot afford a lamb, then he shall bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his guilt offering for that in which he has sinned, two turtledoves or two young pigeons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2838F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2838F\"></sup>one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He shall bring them to the priest, who shall offer first that which is for the sin offering and shall nip its head at the front of its neck, but he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2839G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2839G\"></sup>shall not sever <i>it</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He shall also sprinkle some of the blood of the sin offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2840H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2840H\"></sup>on the side of the altar, while the rest of the blood shall be drained out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2840I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2840I\"></sup>at the base of the altar: it is a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The second he shall then prepare as a burnt offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2841J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2841J\"></sup>according to the ordinance. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2841K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2841K\"></sup>So the priest shall make atonement on his behalf for his sin which he has committed, and it will be forgiven him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2842L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2842L\"></sup>if his means are insufficient for two turtledoves or two young pigeons, then for his offering for that which he has sinned, he shall bring the tenth of an ephah of fine flour for a sin offering; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2842M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2842M\"></sup>he shall not put oil on it or place incense on it, for it is a sin offering.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall bring it to the priest, and the priest shall take his handful of it as its memorial portion and offer <i>it</i> up in smoke on the altar, with the offerings of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by fire: it is a sin offering.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the priest shall make atonement for him concerning his sin which he has committed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2844N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2844N\"></sup>one of these, and it will be forgiven him; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2844O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2844O\"></sup><i>the rest</i> shall become the priest’s, like the grain offering.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2846P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2846P\"></sup>If a person acts unfaithfully and sins <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2846Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2846Q\"></sup>unintentionally against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> holy things, then he shall bring his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2846R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2846R\"></sup>guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2846S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2846S\"></sup>a ram without defect from the flock, according to your valuation in silver by shekels, in <i>terms of</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2846T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2846T\"></sup>shekel of the sanctuary, for a guilt offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2847U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2847U\"></sup>He shall make restitution for that which he has sinned against the holy thing, and shall add to it a fifth part of it and give it to the priest. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2847V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2847V\"></sup>The priest shall then make atonement for him with the ram of the guilt offering, and it will be forgiven him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Now if a person sins and does any of the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded not to be done, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2848W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2848W\"></sup>though he was unaware, still he is guilty and shall bear his punishment.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He is then to bring to the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2849X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2849X\"></sup>a ram without defect from the flock, according to your valuation, for a guilt offering. So the priest shall make atonement for him concerning his error in which he sinned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2849Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2849Y\"></sup>unintentionally and did not know <i>it</i>, and it will be forgiven him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is a guilt offering; he was certainly guilty before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2852A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2852A\"></sup>When a person sins and acts unfaithfully against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and deceives his companion in regard to a deposit or a security entrusted <i>to him</i>, or through robbery, or <i>if</i> he has extorted from his companion,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2853B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2853B\"></sup>has found what was lost and lied about it and sworn falsely, so that he sins in regard to any one of the things a man may do;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then it shall be, when he sins and becomes guilty, that he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2854C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2854C\"></sup>restore what he took by robbery or what he got by extortion, or the deposit which was entrusted to him or the lost thing which he found,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>or anything about which he swore falsely; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2855D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2855D\"></sup>he shall make restitution for it in full and add to it one-fifth more. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2855E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2855E\"></sup>He shall give it to the one to whom it belongs on the day <i>he presents</i> his guilt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then he shall bring to the priest his guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2856F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2856F\"></sup>a ram without defect from the flock, according to your valuation, for a guilt offering,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2857G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2857G\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he will be forgiven for any one of the things which he may have done to incur guilt.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Command Aaron and his sons, saying, ‘This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2859H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2859H\"></sup>the law for the burnt offering: the burnt offering itself <i>shall remain</i> on the hearth on the altar all night until the morning, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2859I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2859I\"></sup>the fire on the altar is to be kept burning on it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The priest is to put on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2860J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2860J\"></sup>his linen robe, and he shall put on undergarments next to his flesh; and he shall take up the ashes <i>to</i> which the fire reduces the burnt offering on the altar and place them beside the altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then he shall take off his garments and put on other garments, and carry the ashes outside the camp to a clean place.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The fire on the altar shall be kept burning on it. It shall not go out, but the priest shall burn wood on it every morning; and he shall lay out the burnt offering on it, and offer up in smoke the fat portions of the peace offerings <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2862K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2862K\"></sup>on it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Fire shall be kept burning continually on the altar; it is not to go out.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘Now this is the law of the grain offering: the sons of Aaron shall present it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2865L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2865L\"></sup>Then one <i>of them</i> shall lift up from it a handful of the fine flour of the grain offering, with its oil and all the incense that is on the grain offering, and he shall offer <i>it</i> up in smoke on the altar, a soothing aroma, as its memorial offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2866M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2866M\"></sup>What is left of it Aaron and his sons are to eat. It shall be eaten as unleavened cakes in a holy place; they are to eat it in the court of the tent of meeting.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2867N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2867N\"></sup>It shall not be baked with leaven. I have given it as their share from My offerings by fire; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2867O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2867O\"></sup>it is most holy, like the sin offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2867P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2867P\"></sup>the guilt offering.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2868Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2868Q\"></sup>Every male among the sons of Aaron may eat it; it is a permanent ordinance throughout your generations, from the offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2868R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2868R\"></sup>Whoever touches them will become consecrated.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“This is the offering which Aaron and his sons are to present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the day when he is anointed; the tenth of an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2870S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2870S\"></sup>ephah of fine flour as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2870T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2870T\"></sup>a regular grain offering, half of it in the morning and half of it in the evening.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It shall be prepared with oil on a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2871U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2871U\"></sup>griddle. When it is <i>well</i> stirred, you shall bring it. You shall present the grain offering in baked pieces as a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The anointed priest who will be in his place among his sons shall offer it. By a permanent ordinance it shall be entirely offered up in smoke to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So every grain offering of the priest shall be burned entirely. It shall not be eaten.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and to his sons, saying, ‘This is the law of the sin offering: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2875V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2875V\"></sup>in the place where the burnt offering is slain the sin offering shall be slain before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is most holy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2876W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2876W\"></sup>The priest who offers it for sin shall eat it. It shall be eaten in a holy place, in the court of the tent of meeting.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2877X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2877X\"></sup>Anyone who touches its flesh will become consecrated; and when any of its blood splashes on a garment, in a holy place you shall wash what was splashed on.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2878Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2878Y\"></sup>the earthenware vessel in which it was boiled shall be broken; and if it was boiled in a bronze vessel, then it shall be scoured and rinsed in water.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2879Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2879Z\"></sup>Every male among the priests may eat of it; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2879AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2879AA\"></sup>it is most holy.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But no sin offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2880AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2880AB\"></sup>of which any of the blood is brought into the tent of meeting to make atonement <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2880AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2880AC\"></sup>in the holy place shall be eaten; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2880AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2880AD\"></sup>it shall be burned with fire."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>‘Now this is the law of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2881A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2881A\"></sup>guilt offering; it is most holy.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2882B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2882B\"></sup>the place where they slay the burnt offering they are to slay the guilt offering, and he shall sprinkle its blood around on the altar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he shall offer from it all its fat: the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2883C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2883C\"></sup>fat tail and the fat that covers the entrails,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the two kidneys with the fat that is on them, which is on the loins, and the lobe on the liver he shall remove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2884D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2884D\"></sup>with the kidneys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The priest shall offer them up in smoke on the altar as an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is a guilt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2886E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2886E\"></sup>Every male among the priests may eat of it. It shall be eaten in a holy place; it is most holy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The guilt offering is like the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2887F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2887F\"></sup>sin offering, there is one law for them; the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2887G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2887G\"></sup>priest who makes atonement with it shall have it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Also the priest who presents any man’s burnt offering, that priest shall have for himself the skin of the burnt offering which he has presented.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Likewise, every grain offering that is baked in the oven and everything prepared in a pan or on a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2889H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2889H\"></sup>griddle shall belong to the priest who presents it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Every grain offering, mixed with oil or dry, shall belong to all the sons of Aaron, to all alike.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘Now this is the law of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2891I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2891I\"></sup>sacrifice of peace offerings which shall be presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If he offers it by way of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2892J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2892J\"></sup>thanksgiving, then along with the sacrifice of thanksgiving he shall offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2892K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2892K\"></sup>unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers spread with oil, and cakes <i>of well</i> stirred fine flour mixed with oil.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>With the sacrifice of his peace offerings for thanksgiving, he shall present his offering with cakes of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2893L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2893L\"></sup>leavened bread.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Of this he shall present one of every offering as a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2894M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2894M\"></sup>it shall belong to the priest who sprinkles the blood of the peace offerings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2895N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2895N\"></sup>Now <i>as for</i> the flesh of the sacrifice of his thanksgiving peace offerings, it shall be eaten on the day of his offering; he shall not leave any of it over until morning.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if the sacrifice of his offering is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2896O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2896O\"></sup>votive or a freewill offering, it shall be eaten on the day that he offers his sacrifice, and on the next day what is left of it may be eaten;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2897P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2897P\"></sup>but what is left over from the flesh of the sacrifice on the third day shall be burned with fire.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So if any of the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offerings should <i>ever</i> be eaten on the third day, he who offers it will not be accepted, <i>and</i> it will not be reckoned to his <i>benefit</i>. It shall be an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2898Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2898Q\"></sup>offensive thing, and the person who eats of it will bear his <i>own</i> iniquity.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘Also the flesh that touches anything unclean shall not be eaten; it shall be burned with fire. As for <i>other</i> flesh, anyone who is clean may eat <i>such</i> flesh.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2900R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2900R\"></sup>But the person who eats the flesh of the sacrifice of peace offerings which belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in his uncleanness, that person <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2900S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2900S\"></sup>shall be cut off from his people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2901T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2901T\"></sup>When anyone touches anything unclean, whether human uncleanness, or an unclean animal, or any unclean detestable thing, and eats of the flesh of the sacrifice of peace offerings which belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that person shall be cut off from his people.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘You shall not eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2903U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2903U\"></sup>any fat <i>from</i> an ox, a sheep or a goat.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Also the fat of <i>an animal</i> which dies and the fat of an animal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2904V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2904V\"></sup>torn <i>by beasts</i> may be put to any other use, but you must certainly not eat it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For whoever eats the fat of the animal from which an offering by fire is offered to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, even the person who eats shall be cut off from his people.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2906W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2906W\"></sup>You are not to eat any blood, either of bird or animal, in any of your dwellings.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Any person who eats any blood, even that person shall be cut off from his people.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘He who offers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2909X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2909X\"></sup>the sacrifice of his peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall bring his offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from the sacrifice of his peace offerings.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>His own hands are to bring offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. He shall bring the fat with the breast, that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2910Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2910Y\"></sup>breast may be presented as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The priest shall offer up the fat in smoke on the altar, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2911Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2911Z\"></sup>the breast shall belong to Aaron and his sons.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You shall give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2912AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2912AA\"></sup>the right thigh to the priest as a contribution from the sacrifices of your peace offerings.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The one among the sons of Aaron who offers the blood of the peace offerings and the fat, the right thigh shall be his as <i>his</i> portion.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For I have taken <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2914AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2914AB\"></sup>the breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the contribution from the sons of Israel from the sacrifices of their peace offerings, and have given them to Aaron the priest and to his sons as <i>their</i> due forever from the sons of Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>‘This is that which is consecrated to Aaron and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2915AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2915AC\"></sup>which is consecrated to his sons from the offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in that day when he presented them to serve as priests to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>These the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded to be given them from the sons of Israel in the day that He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2916AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2916AD\"></sup>anointed them. It is <i>their</i> due forever throughout their generations.’”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>This is the law of the burnt offering, the grain offering and the sin offering and the guilt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2917AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2917AE\"></sup>the ordination offering and the sacrifice of peace offerings,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2918AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2918AF\"></sup>which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses at Mount Sinai in the day that He commanded the sons of Israel to present their offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the wilderness of Sinai."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2920A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2920A\"></sup>Take Aaron and his sons with him, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2920B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2920B\"></sup>garments and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2920C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2920C\"></sup>the anointing oil and the bull of the sin offering, and the two rams and the basket of unleavened bread,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and assemble all the congregation at the doorway of the tent of meeting.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him. When the congregation was assembled at the doorway of the tent of meeting,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moses said to the congregation, “This is the thing which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to do.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2924D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2924D\"></sup>Moses had Aaron and his sons come near and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2924E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2924E\"></sup>washed them with water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2925F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2925F\"></sup>put the tunic on him and girded him with the sash, and clothed him with the robe and put the ephod on him; and he girded him with the artistic band of the ephod, with which he tied <i>it</i> to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He then placed the breastpiece on him, and in the breastpiece he put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2926G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2926G\"></sup>the Urim and the Thummim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He also placed the turban on his head, and on the turban, at its front, he placed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2927H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2927H\"></sup>the golden plate, the holy crown, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moses then took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2928I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2928I\"></sup>the anointing oil and anointed the tabernacle and all that was in it, and consecrated them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He sprinkled some of it on the altar seven times and anointed the altar and all its utensils, and the basin and its stand, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2929J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2929J\"></sup>consecrate them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he poured some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2930K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2930K\"></sup>anointing oil on Aaron’s head and anointed him, to consecrate him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2931L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2931L\"></sup>Next Moses had Aaron’s sons come near and clothed them with tunics, and girded them with sashes and bound caps on them, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2932M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2932M\"></sup>the bull of the sin offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the bull of the sin offering.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Next Moses slaughtered <i>it</i> and took the blood and with his finger <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2933N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2933N\"></sup>put <i>some of it</i> around on the horns of the altar, and purified the altar. Then he poured out <i>the rest of</i> the blood at the base of the altar and consecrated it, to make atonement for it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2934O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2934O\"></sup>took all the fat that was on the entrails and the lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and their fat; and Moses offered it up in smoke on the altar.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2935P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2935P\"></sup>But the bull and its hide and its flesh and its refuse he burned in the fire outside the camp, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he presented <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2936Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2936Q\"></sup>the ram of the burnt offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moses slaughtered <i>it</i> and sprinkled the blood around on the altar.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When he had cut the ram into its pieces, Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2938R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2938R\"></sup>offered up the head and the pieces and the suet in smoke.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After he had washed the entrails and the legs with water, Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2939S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2939S\"></sup>offered up the whole ram in smoke on the altar. It was a burnt offering for a soothing aroma; it was an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then he presented the second ram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2940T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2940T\"></sup>the ram of ordination, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the head of the ram.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses slaughtered <i>it</i> and took some of its blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2941U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2941U\"></sup>put it on the lobe of Aaron’s right ear, and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He also had Aaron’s sons come near; and Moses put some of the blood on the lobe of their right ear, and on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot. Moses then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2942V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2942V\"></sup>sprinkled <i>the rest of</i> the blood around on the altar.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He took the fat, and the fat tail, and all the fat that was on the entrails, and the lobe of the liver and the two kidneys and their fat and the right thigh.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2944W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2944W\"></sup>From the basket of unleavened bread that was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he took one unleavened cake and one cake of bread <i>mixed with</i> oil and one wafer, and placed <i>them</i> on the portions of fat and on the right thigh.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2945X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2945X\"></sup>put all <i>these</i> on the hands of Aaron and on the hands of his sons and presented them as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2946Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2946Y\"></sup>took them from their hands and offered them up in smoke on the altar with the burnt offering. They were an ordination offering for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2946Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2946Z\"></sup>a soothing aroma; it was an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses also took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2947AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2947AA\"></sup>the breast and presented it for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2947AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2947AB\"></sup>Moses’ portion of the ram of ordination, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2948AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2948AC\"></sup>took some of the anointing oil and some of the blood which was on the altar and sprinkled it on Aaron, on his garments, on his sons, and on the garments of his sons with him; and he consecrated Aaron, his garments, and his sons, and the garments of his sons with him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron and to his sons, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2949AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2949AD\"></sup>Boil the flesh at the doorway of the tent of meeting, and eat it there together with the bread which is in the basket of the ordination offering, just as I commanded, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2949AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2949AE\"></sup>saying, ‘Aaron and his sons shall eat it.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2950AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2950AF\"></sup>The remainder of the flesh and of the bread you shall burn in the fire.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2951AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2951AG\"></sup>You shall not go outside the doorway of the tent of meeting for seven days, until the day that the period of your ordination is fulfilled; for he will ordain you through seven days.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to do as has been done this day, to make atonement on your behalf.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>At the doorway of the tent of meeting, moreover, you shall remain day and night for seven days and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2953AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2953AH\"></sup>keep the charge of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that you will not die, for so I have been commanded.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Thus Aaron and his sons did all the things which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now it came about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2955A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2955A\"></sup>on the eighth day that Moses called Aaron and his sons and the elders of Israel;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he said to Aaron, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2956B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2956B\"></sup>Take for yourself a calf, a bull, for a sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering, <i>both</i> without defect, and offer <i>them</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then to the sons of Israel you shall speak, saying, ‘Take a male goat for a sin offering, and a calf and a lamb, both one year old, without defect, for a burnt offering,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and an ox and a ram for peace offerings, to sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and a grain offering mixed with oil; for today <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2958C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2958C\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will appear to you.’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they took what Moses had commanded to the front of the tent of meeting, and the whole congregation came near and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moses said, “This is the thing which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded you to do, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2960D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2960D\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may appear to you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moses then said to Aaron, “Come near to the altar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2961E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2961E\"></sup>offer your sin offering and your burnt offering, that you may make atonement for yourself and for the people; then make the offering for the people, that you may make atonement for them, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2962F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2962F\"></sup>So Aaron came near to the altar and slaughtered the calf of the sin offering which was for himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2963G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2963G\"></sup>Aaron’s sons presented the blood to him; and he dipped his finger in the blood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2963H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2963H\"></sup>put <i>some</i> on the horns of the altar, and poured out <i>the rest of</i> the blood at the base of the altar.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The fat and the kidneys and the lobe of the liver of the sin offering, he then offered up in smoke on the altar just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2965I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2965I\"></sup>The flesh and the skin, however, he burned with fire outside the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he slaughtered the burnt offering; and Aaron’s sons handed the blood to him and he sprinkled it around on the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They handed the burnt offering to him in pieces, with the head, and he offered <i>them</i> up in smoke on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He also washed the entrails and the legs, and offered <i>them</i> up in smoke with the burnt offering on the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he presented the people’s offering, and took the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2969J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2969J\"></sup>goat of the sin offering which was for the people, and slaughtered it and offered it for sin, like the first.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also presented the burnt offering, and offered it according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2970K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2970K\"></sup>the ordinance.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Next he presented <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2971L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2971L\"></sup>the grain offering, and filled his hand with some of it and offered <i>it</i> up in smoke on the altar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2971M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2971M\"></sup>besides the burnt offering of the morning.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2972N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2972N\"></sup>he slaughtered the ox and the ram, the sacrifice of peace offerings which was for the people; and Aaron’s sons handed the blood to him and he sprinkled it around on the altar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As for the portions of fat from the ox and from the ram, the fat tail, and the <i>fat</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2973O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2973O\"></sup>covering, and the kidneys and the lobe of the liver,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>they now placed the portions of fat on the breasts; and he offered them up in smoke on the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2975P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2975P\"></sup>the breasts and the right thigh Aaron presented as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as Moses had commanded.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Aaron lifted up his hands toward the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2976Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2976Q\"></sup>blessed them, and he stepped down after making the sin offering and the burnt offering and the peace offerings.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses and Aaron went into the tent of meeting. When they came out and blessed the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2977R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2977R\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to all the people.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2978S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2978S\"></sup>Then fire came out from before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed the burnt offering and the portions of fat on the altar; and when all the people saw <i>it</i>, they shouted and fell on their faces."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2979A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2979A\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, the sons of Aaron, took their respective <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2979B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2979B\"></sup>firepans, and after putting fire in them, placed incense on it and offered strange fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which He had not commanded them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2980C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2980C\"></sup>And fire came out from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed them, and they died before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron, “It is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke, saying,‘By those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2981D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2981D\"></sup>come near Me I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2981E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2981E\"></sup>will be treated as holy,And before all the people I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2981F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2981F\"></sup>be honored.’”So Aaron, therefore, kept silent.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses called also to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2982G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2982G\"></sup>Mishael and Elzaphan, the sons of Aaron’s uncle Uzziel, and said to them, “Come forward, carry your relatives away from the front of the sanctuary to the outside of the camp.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they came forward and carried them still in their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2983H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2983H\"></sup>tunics to the outside of the camp, as Moses had said.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron and to his sons Eleazar and Ithamar, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2984I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2984I\"></sup>Do not uncover your heads nor tear your clothes, so that you will not die and that He will not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2984J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2984J\"></sup>become wrathful against all the congregation. But your kinsmen, the whole house of Israel, shall bewail the burning which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought about.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall not even go out from the doorway of the tent of meeting, or you will die; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2985K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2985K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointing oil is upon you.” So they did according to the word of Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> then spoke to Aaron, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2987L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2987L\"></sup>Do not drink wine or strong drink, neither you nor your sons with you, when you come into the tent of meeting, so that you will not die—it is a perpetual statute throughout your generations—",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2988M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2988M\"></sup>so as to make a distinction between the holy and the profane, and between the unclean and the clean,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2989N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2989N\"></sup>so as to teach the sons of Israel all the statutes which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken to them through Moses.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Moses spoke to Aaron, and to his surviving sons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2990O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2990O\"></sup>Eleazar and Ithamar, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2990P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2990P\"></sup>Take the grain offering that is left over from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> offerings by fire and eat it unleavened beside the altar, for it is most holy.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall eat it, moreover, in a holy place, because it is your due and your sons’ due out of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> offerings by fire; for thus I have been commanded.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2992Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2992Q\"></sup>The breast of the wave offering, however, and the thigh of the offering you may eat in a clean place, you and your sons and your daughters with you; for they have been given as your due and your sons’ due out of the sacrifices of the peace offerings of the sons of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2993R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2993R\"></sup>The thigh offered by lifting up and the breast offered by waving they shall bring along with the offerings by fire of the portions of fat, to present as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; so it shall be a thing perpetually due you and your sons with you, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Moses searched carefully for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2994S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2994S\"></sup>goat of the sin offering, and behold, it had been burned up! So he was angry with Aaron’s surviving sons Eleazar and Ithamar, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Why <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2995T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2995T\"></sup>did you not eat the sin offering at the holy place? For it is most holy, and He gave it to you to bear away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2995U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2995U\"></sup>the guilt of the congregation, to make atonement for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2996V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2996V\"></sup>since its blood had not been brought inside, into the sanctuary, you should certainly have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2996W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2996W\"></sup>eaten it in the sanctuary, just as I commanded.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Aaron spoke to Moses, “Behold, this very day they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2997X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2997X\"></sup>presented their sin offering and their burnt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. When things like these happened to me, if I had eaten a sin offering today, would it have been good in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Moses heard <i>that</i>, it seemed good in his sight."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke again to Moses and to Aaron, saying to them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3000A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3000A\"></sup>These are the creatures which you may eat from all the animals that are on the earth.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Whatever divides a hoof, thus making split hoofs, <i>and</i> chews the cud, among the animals, that you may eat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3002B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3002B\"></sup>you are not to eat of these, among those which chew the cud, or among those which divide the hoof: the camel, for though it chews cud, it does not divide the hoof, it is unclean to you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Likewise, the shaphan, for though it chews cud, it does not divide the hoof, it is unclean to you;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>the rabbit also, for though it chews cud, it does not divide the hoof, it is unclean to you;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and the pig, for though it divides the hoof, thus making a split hoof, it does not chew cud, it is unclean to you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall not eat of their flesh nor touch their carcasses; they are unclean to you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3007C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3007C\"></sup>These you may eat, whatever is in the water: all that have fins and scales, those in the water, in the seas or in the rivers, you may eat.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3008D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3008D\"></sup>But whatever is in the seas and in the rivers that does not have fins and scales among all the teeming life of the water, and among all the living creatures that are in the water, they are detestable things to you,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and they shall be abhorrent to you; you may not eat of their flesh, and their carcasses you shall detest.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Whatever in the water does not have fins and scales is abhorrent to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘These, moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3011E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3011E\"></sup>you shall detest among the birds; they are abhorrent, not to be eaten: the eagle and the vulture and the buzzard,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and the kite and the falcon in its kind,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>every raven in its kind,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and the ostrich and the owl and the sea gull and the hawk in its kind,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the little owl and the cormorant and the great owl,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the white owl and the pelican and the carrion vulture,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the stork, the heron in its kinds, and the hoopoe, and the bat.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>‘All the winged insects that walk on <i>all</i> fours are detestable to you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Yet these you may eat among all the winged insects which walk on <i>all</i> fours: those which have above their feet jointed legs with which to jump on the earth.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These of them you may eat: the locust in its kinds, and the devastating locust in its kinds, and the cricket in its kinds, and the grasshopper in its kinds.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But all other winged insects which are four-footed are detestable to you.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘By these, moreover, you will be made unclean: whoever touches their carcasses becomes unclean until evening,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3023F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3023F\"></sup>whoever picks up any of their carcasses shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Concerning all the animals which divide the hoof but do not make a split <i>hoof</i>, or which do not chew cud, they are unclean to you: whoever touches them becomes unclean.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Also whatever walks on its paws, among all the creatures that walk on <i>all</i> fours, are unclean to you; whoever touches their carcasses becomes unclean until evening,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the one who picks up their carcasses shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening; they are unclean to you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>‘Now these are to you the unclean among the swarming things which swarm on the earth: the mole, and the mouse, and the great lizard in its kinds,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and the gecko, and the crocodile, and the lizard, and the sand reptile, and the chameleon.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are to you the unclean among all the swarming things; whoever touches them when they are dead becomes unclean until evening.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Also anything on which one of them may fall when they are dead becomes unclean, including any wooden article, or clothing, or a skin, or a sack—any article of which use is made—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3030G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3030G\"></sup>it shall be put in the water and be unclean until evening, then it becomes clean.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As for any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3031H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3031H\"></sup>earthenware vessel into which one of them may fall, whatever is in it becomes unclean and you shall break the vessel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Any of the food which may be eaten, on which water comes, shall become unclean, and any liquid which may be drunk in every vessel shall become unclean.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Everything, moreover, on which part of their carcass may fall becomes unclean; an oven or a stove shall be smashed; they are unclean and shall continue as unclean to you.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Nevertheless a spring or a cistern collecting water shall be clean, though the one who touches their carcass shall be unclean.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>If a part of their carcass falls on any seed for sowing which is to be sown, it is clean.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Though if water is put on the seed and a part of their carcass falls on it, it is unclean to you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>‘Also if one of the animals dies which you have for food, the one who touches its carcass becomes unclean until evening.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3038I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3038I\"></sup>He too, who eats some of its carcass shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening, and the one who picks up its carcass shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3039J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3039J\"></sup>Now every swarming thing that swarms on the earth is detestable, not to be eaten.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Whatever crawls on its belly, and whatever walks on <i>all</i> fours, whatever has many feet, in respect to every swarming thing that swarms on the earth, you shall not eat them, for they are detestable.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3041K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3041K\"></sup>Do not render yourselves detestable through any of the swarming things that swarm; and you shall not make yourselves unclean with them so that you become unclean.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3042L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3042L\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. Consecrate yourselves therefore, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3042M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3042M\"></sup>be holy, for I am holy. And you shall not make yourselves unclean with any of the swarming things that swarm on the earth.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3043N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3043N\"></sup>For I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who brought you up from the land of Egypt to be your God; thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3043O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3043O\"></sup>you shall be holy, for I am holy.’”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>This is the law regarding the animal and the bird, and every living thing that moves in the waters and everything that swarms on the earth,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3045P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3045P\"></sup>to make a distinction between the unclean and the clean, and between the edible creature and the creature which is not to be eaten."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying:‘When a woman gives birth and bears a male <i>child</i>, then she shall be unclean for seven days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3047A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3047A\"></sup>as in the days of her menstruation she shall be unclean.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>On <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3048B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3048B\"></sup>the eighth day the flesh of his foreskin shall be circumcised.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then she shall remain in the blood of <i>her</i> purification for thirty-three days; she shall not touch any consecrated thing, nor enter the sanctuary until the days of her purification are completed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if she bears a female <i>child</i>, then she shall be unclean for two weeks, as in her menstruation; and she shall remain in the blood of <i>her</i> purification for sixty-six days.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3051C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3051C\"></sup>When the days of her purification are completed, for a son or for a daughter, she shall bring to the priest at the doorway of the tent of meeting a one year old lamb for a burnt offering and a young pigeon or a turtledove <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3051D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3051D\"></sup>for a sin offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he shall offer it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and make atonement for her, and she shall be cleansed from the flow of her blood. This is the law for her who bears <i>a child, whether</i> a male or a female.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if she cannot afford a lamb, then she shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3053E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3053E\"></sup>two turtledoves or two young pigeons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3053F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3053F\"></sup>the one for a burnt offering and the other for a sin offering; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3053G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3053G\"></sup>priest shall make atonement for her, and she will be clean.’”"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“When a man has on the skin of his body a swelling or a scab or a bright spot, and it becomes an infection of leprosy on the skin of his body, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3055A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3055A\"></sup>then he shall be brought to Aaron the priest or to one of his sons the priests.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The priest shall look at the mark on the skin of the body, and if the hair in the infection has turned white and the infection appears to be deeper than the skin of his body, it is an infection of leprosy; when the priest has looked at him, he shall pronounce him unclean.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But if the bright spot is white on the skin of his body, and it does not appear to be deeper than the skin, and the hair on it has not turned white, then the priest shall isolate <i>him who has</i> the infection for seven days.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The priest shall look at him on the seventh day, and if in his eyes the infection has not changed <i>and</i> the infection has not spread on the skin, then the priest shall isolate him for seven more days.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priest shall look at him again on the seventh day, and if the infection has faded and the mark has not spread on the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him clean; it is <i>only</i> a scab. And he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3059B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3059B\"></sup>wash his clothes and be clean.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“But if the scab spreads farther on the skin after he has shown himself to the priest for his cleansing, he shall appear again to the priest.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The priest shall look, and if the scab has spread on the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is leprosy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When the infection of leprosy is on a man, then he shall be brought to the priest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The priest shall then look, and if there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3063C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3063C\"></sup>white swelling in the skin, and it has turned the hair white, and there is quick raw flesh in the swelling,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>it is a chronic leprosy on the skin of his body, and the priest shall pronounce him unclean; he shall not isolate him, for he is unclean.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If the leprosy breaks out farther on the skin, and the leprosy covers all the skin of <i>him who has</i> the infection from his head even to his feet, as far as the priest can see,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>then the priest shall look, and behold, <i>if</i> the leprosy has covered all his body, he shall pronounce clean <i>him who has</i> the infection; it has all turned white <i>and</i> he is clean.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But whenever raw flesh appears on him, he shall be unclean.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest shall look at the raw flesh, and he shall pronounce him unclean; the raw flesh is unclean, it is leprosy.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Or if the raw flesh turns again and is changed to white, then he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3069D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3069D\"></sup>come to the priest,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the priest shall look at him, and behold, <i>if</i> the infection has turned to white, then the priest shall pronounce clean <i>him who has</i> the infection; he is clean.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“When the body has a boil on its skin and it is healed,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and in the place of the boil there is a white swelling or a reddish-white, bright spot, then it shall be shown to the priest;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the priest shall look, and behold, <i>if</i> it appears to be lower than the skin, and the hair on it has turned white, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is the infection of leprosy, it has broken out in the boil.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But if the priest looks at it, and behold, there are no white hairs in it and it is not lower than the skin and is faded, then the priest shall isolate him for seven days;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and if it spreads farther on the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infection.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But if the bright spot remains in its place and does not spread, it is <i>only</i> the scar of the boil; and the priest shall pronounce him clean.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Or if the body sustains in its skin a burn by fire, and the raw <i>flesh</i> of the burn becomes a bright spot, reddish-white, or white,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>then the priest shall look at it. And if the hair in the bright spot has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3078E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3078E\"></sup>turned white and it appears to be deeper than the skin, it is leprosy; it has broken out in the burn. Therefore, the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infection of leprosy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if the priest looks at it, and indeed, there is no white hair in the bright spot and it is no deeper than the skin, but is dim, then the priest shall isolate him for seven days;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the priest shall look at him on the seventh day. If it spreads farther in the skin, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is an infection of leprosy.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if the bright spot remains in its place and has not spread in the skin, but is dim, it is the swelling from the burn; and the priest shall pronounce him clean, for it is <i>only</i> the scar of the burn.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Now if a man or woman has an infection on the head or on the beard,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>then the priest shall look at the infection, and if it appears to be deeper than the skin and there is thin yellowish hair in it, then the priest shall pronounce him unclean; it is a scale, it is leprosy of the head or of the beard.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But if the priest looks at the infection of the scale, and indeed, it appears to be no deeper than the skin and there is no black hair in it, then the priest shall isolate <i>the person</i> with the scaly infection for seven days.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>On the seventh day the priest shall look at the infection, and if the scale has not spread and no yellowish hair has grown in it, and the appearance of the scale is no deeper than the skin,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>then he shall shave himself, but he shall not shave the scale; and the priest shall isolate <i>the person</i> with the scale seven more days.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then on the seventh day the priest shall look at the scale, and if the scale has not spread in the skin and it appears to be no deeper than the skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean; and he shall wash his clothes and be clean.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But if the scale spreads farther in the skin after his cleansing,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>then the priest shall look at him, and if the scale has spread in the skin, the priest need not seek for the yellowish hair; he is unclean.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>If in his sight the scale has remained, however, and black hair has grown in it, the scale has healed, he is clean; and the priest shall pronounce him clean.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“When a man or a woman has bright spots on the skin of the body, <i>even</i> white bright spots,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then the priest shall look, and if the bright spots on the skin of their bodies are a faint white, it is eczema that has broken out on the skin; he is clean.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“Now if a man loses the hair of his head, he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3093F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3093F\"></sup>bald; he is clean.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>If his head becomes bald at the front and sides, he is bald on the forehead; he is clean.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>But if on the bald head or the bald forehead, there occurs a reddish-white infection, it is leprosy breaking out on his bald head or on his bald forehead.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3096G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3096G\"></sup>the priest shall look at him; and if the swelling of the infection is reddish-white on his bald head or on his bald forehead, like the appearance of leprosy in the skin of the body,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>he is a leprous man, he is unclean. The priest shall surely pronounce him unclean; his infection is on his head.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“As for the leper who has the infection, his clothes shall be torn, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3098H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3098H\"></sup>the hair of his head shall be uncovered, and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3098I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3098I\"></sup>cover his mustache and cry, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3098J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3098J\"></sup>Unclean! Unclean!’",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He shall remain unclean all the days during which he has the infection; he is unclean. He shall live alone; his dwelling shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3099K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3099K\"></sup>outside the camp.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“When a garment has a mark of leprosy in it, whether it is a wool garment or a linen garment,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>whether in warp or woof, of linen or of wool, whether in leather or in any article made of leather,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>if the mark is greenish or reddish in the garment or in the leather, or in the warp or in the woof, or in any article of leather, it is a leprous mark and shall be shown to the priest.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3103L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3103L\"></sup>the priest shall look at the mark and shall quarantine the article with the mark for seven days.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>He shall then look at the mark on the seventh day; if the mark has spread in the garment, whether in the warp or in the woof, or in the leather, whatever the purpose for which the leather is used, the mark is a leprous malignancy, it is unclean.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>So he shall burn the garment, whether the warp or the woof, in wool or in linen, or any article of leather in which the mark occurs, for it is a leprous malignancy; it shall be burned in the fire.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>“But if the priest shall look, and indeed the mark has not spread in the garment, either in the warp or in the woof, or in any article of leather,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>then the priest shall order them to wash the thing in which the mark occurs and he shall quarantine it for seven more days.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>After the article with the mark has been washed, the priest shall again look, and if the mark has not changed its appearance, even though the mark has not spread, it is unclean; you shall burn it in the fire, whether an eating away has produced bareness on the top or on the front of it.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>“Then if the priest looks, and if the mark has faded after it has been washed, then he shall tear it out of the garment or out of the leather, whether from the warp or from the woof;",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>and if it appears again in the garment, whether in the warp or in the woof, or in any article of leather, it is an outbreak; the article with the mark shall be burned in the fire.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>The garment, whether the warp or the woof, or any article of leather from which the mark has departed when you washed it, it shall then be washed a second time and will be clean.”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>This is the law for the mark of leprosy in a garment of wool or linen, whether in the warp or in the woof, or in any article of leather, for pronouncing it clean or unclean."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“This shall be the law of the leper in the day of his cleansing. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3114A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3114A\"></sup>Now he shall be brought to the priest,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the priest shall go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3115B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3115B\"></sup>out to the outside of the camp. Thus the priest shall look, and if the infection of leprosy has been healed in the leper,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then the priest shall give orders to take two live clean birds and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3116C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3116C\"></sup>cedar wood and a scarlet string and hyssop for the one who is to be cleansed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The priest shall also give orders to slay the one bird in an earthenware vessel over running water.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><i>As for</i> the live bird, he shall take it together with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3118D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3118D\"></sup>the cedar wood and the scarlet string and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3118E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3118E\"></sup>hyssop, and shall dip them and the live bird in the blood of the bird that was slain over the running water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3119F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3119F\"></sup>He shall then sprinkle seven times the one who is to be cleansed from the leprosy and shall pronounce him clean, and shall let the live bird go free over the open field.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3120G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3120G\"></sup>The one to be cleansed shall then wash his clothes and shave off all his hair and bathe in water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3120H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3120H\"></sup>be clean. Now afterward, he may enter the camp, but he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3120I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3120I\"></sup>shall stay outside his tent for seven days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It will be on the seventh day that he shall shave off all his hair: he shall shave his head and his beard and his eyebrows, even all his hair. He shall then wash his clothes and bathe his body in water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3121J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3121J\"></sup>be clean.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Now on the eighth day he is to take two male lambs without defect, and a yearling ewe lamb without defect, and three-tenths <i>of an</i> <i>ephah</i> of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering, and one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3122K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3122K\"></sup>log of oil;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and the priest who pronounces him clean shall present the man to be cleansed and the aforesaid before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the priest shall take the one male lamb and bring it for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3124L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3124L\"></sup>guilt offering, with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3124M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3124M\"></sup>log of oil, and present them as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3124N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3124N\"></sup>wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Next he shall slaughter the male lamb in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3125O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3125O\"></sup>the place where they slaughter the sin offering and the burnt offering, at the place of the sanctuary—for the guilt offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3125P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3125P\"></sup>like the sin offering, belongs to the priest; it is most holy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The priest shall then take some of the blood of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3126Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3126Q\"></sup>guilt offering, and the priest shall put <i>it</i> on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3126R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3126R\"></sup>the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest shall also take some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3127S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3127S\"></sup>log of oil, and pour <i>it</i> into his left palm;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the priest shall then dip his right-hand finger into the oil that is in his left palm, and with his finger sprinkle some of the oil seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Of the remaining oil which is in his palm, the priest shall put some on the right ear lobe of the one to be cleansed, and on the thumb of his right hand, and on the big toe of his right foot, on the blood of the guilt offering;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>while the rest of the oil that is in the priest’s palm, he shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed. So the priest shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3130T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3130T\"></sup>atonement on his behalf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The priest shall next offer the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3131U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3131U\"></sup>sin offering and make atonement for the one to be cleansed from his uncleanness. Then afterward, he shall slaughter the burnt offering.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priest shall offer up the burnt offering and the grain offering on the altar. Thus the priest shall make atonement for him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3132V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3132V\"></sup>he will be clean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3133W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3133W\"></sup>But if he is poor and his means are insufficient, then he is to take one male lamb for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3133X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3133X\"></sup>guilt offering as a wave offering to make atonement for him, and one-tenth <i>of an</i> <i>ephah</i> of fine flour mixed with oil for a grain offering, and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3133Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3133Y\"></sup>log of oil,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and two turtledoves or two young pigeons which are within his means, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3134Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3134Z\"></sup>the one shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3134AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3134AA\"></sup>sin offering and the other a burnt offering.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3135AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3135AB\"></sup>Then the eighth day he shall bring them for his cleansing to the priest, at the doorway of the tent of meeting, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The priest shall take the lamb of the guilt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3136AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3136AC\"></sup>the log of oil, and the priest shall offer them for a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Next he shall slaughter the lamb of the guilt offering; and the priest is to take some of the blood of the guilt offering and put <i>it</i> on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3137AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3137AD\"></sup>the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The priest shall also pour some of the oil into his left palm;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and with his right-hand finger the priest shall sprinkle some of the oil that is in his left palm seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The priest shall then put some of the oil that is in his palm on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, and on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot, on the place of the blood of the guilt offering.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moreover, the rest of the oil that is in the priest’s palm he shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed, to make atonement on his behalf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He shall then offer one of the turtledoves or young pigeons, which are within his means.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><i>He shall offer</i> what he can afford, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3143AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3143AE\"></sup>the one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering, together with the grain offering. So the priest shall make atonement before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on behalf of the one to be cleansed.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the law <i>for him</i> in whom there is an infection of leprosy, whose means are limited for his cleansing.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> further spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying:",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3146AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3146AF\"></sup>When you enter the land of Canaan, which I give you for a possession, and I put a mark of leprosy on a house in the land of your possession,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>then the one who owns the house shall come and tell the priest, saying, ‘<i>Something</i> like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3147AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3147AG\"></sup>a mark <i>of leprosy</i> has become visible to me in the house.’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The priest shall then command that they empty the house before the priest goes in to look at the mark, so that everything in the house need not become unclean; and afterward the priest shall go in to look at the house.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So he shall look at the mark, and if the mark on the walls of the house has greenish or reddish depressions and appears deeper than the surface,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>then the priest shall come out of the house, to the doorway, and quarantine the house for seven days.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The priest shall return on the seventh day and make an inspection. If the mark has indeed spread in the walls of the house,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>then the priest shall order them to tear out the stones with the mark in them and throw them away at an unclean place outside the city.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He shall have the house scraped all around inside, and they shall dump the plaster that they scrape off at an unclean place outside the city.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then they shall take other stones and replace <i>those</i> stones, and he shall take other plaster and replaster the house.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“If, however, the mark breaks out again in the house after he has torn out the stones and scraped the house, and after it has been replastered,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>then the priest shall come in and make an inspection. If he sees that the mark has indeed spread in the house, it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3156AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3156AH\"></sup>a malignant mark in the house; it is unclean.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>He shall therefore tear down the house, its stones, and its timbers, and all the plaster of the house, and he shall take <i>them</i> outside the city to an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3157AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3157AI\"></sup>unclean place.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Moreover, whoever goes into the house during the time that he has quarantined it, becomes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3158AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3158AJ\"></sup>unclean until evening.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Likewise, whoever lies down in the house shall wash his clothes, and whoever eats in the house shall wash his clothes.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“If, on the other hand, the priest comes in and makes an inspection and the mark has not indeed spread in the house after the house has been replastered, then the priest shall pronounce the house clean because the mark has not reappeared.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>To cleanse the house then, he shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3161AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3161AK\"></sup>two birds and cedar wood and a scarlet string and hyssop,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>and he shall slaughter the one bird in an earthenware vessel over running water.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then he shall take the cedar wood and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3163AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3163AL\"></sup>hyssop and the scarlet string, with the live bird, and dip them in the blood of the slain bird as well as in the running water, and sprinkle the house seven times.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He shall thus cleanse the house with the blood of the bird and with the running water, along with the live bird and with the cedar wood and with the hyssop and with the scarlet string.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>However, he shall let the live bird go free outside the city into the open field. So he shall make atonement for the house, and it will be clean.”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>This is the law for any mark of leprosy—even for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3166AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3166AM\"></sup>scale,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>and for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3167AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3167AN\"></sup>leprous garment or house,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3168AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3168AO\"></sup>for a swelling, and for a scab, and for a bright spot—",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>to teach when they are unclean and when they are clean. This is the law of leprosy."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3171A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3171A\"></sup>When any man has a discharge from his body, his discharge is unclean.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>This, moreover, shall be his uncleanness in his discharge: it is his uncleanness whether his body allows its discharge to flow or whether his body obstructs its discharge.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Every bed on which the person with the discharge lies becomes unclean, and everything on which he sits becomes unclean.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Anyone, moreover, who touches his bed shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and whoever sits on the thing on which the man with the discharge has been sitting, shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Also whoever touches the person with the discharge shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Or if the man with the discharge spits on one who is clean, he too shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Every saddle on which the person with the discharge rides becomes unclean.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whoever then touches any of the things which were under him shall be unclean until evening, and he who carries them shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Likewise, whomever the one with the discharge touches without having rinsed his hands in water shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>However, an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3181B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3181B\"></sup>earthenware vessel which the person with the discharge touches shall be broken, and every wooden vessel shall be rinsed in water.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘Now when the man with the discharge becomes cleansed from his discharge, then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3182C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3182C\"></sup>shall count off for himself seven days for his cleansing; he shall then wash his clothes and bathe his body in running water and will become clean.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then on the eighth day he shall take for himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3183D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3183D\"></sup>two turtledoves or two young pigeons, and come before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the doorway of the tent of meeting and give them to the priest;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the priest shall offer them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3184E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3184E\"></sup>one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3184F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3184F\"></sup>the priest shall make atonement on his behalf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because of his discharge.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3185G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3185G\"></sup>Now if a man has a seminal emission, he shall bathe all his body in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for any garment or any leather on which there is seminal emission, it shall be washed with water and be unclean until evening.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If a man lies with a woman <i>so that</i> there is a seminal emission, they shall both bathe in water and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3187H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3187H\"></sup>unclean until evening.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3188I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3188I\"></sup>When a woman has a discharge, <i>if</i> her discharge in her body is blood, she shall continue in her menstrual impurity for seven days; and whoever touches her shall be unclean until evening.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Everything also on which she lies during her menstrual impurity shall be unclean, and everything on which she sits shall be unclean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Anyone who touches her bed shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Whoever touches any thing on which she sits shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whether it be on the bed or on the thing on which she is sitting, when he touches it, he shall be unclean until evening.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3193J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3193J\"></sup>If a man actually lies with her so that her menstrual impurity is on him, he shall be unclean seven days, and every bed on which he lies shall be unclean.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3194K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3194K\"></sup>Now if a woman has a discharge of her blood many days, not at the period of her menstrual impurity, or if she has a discharge beyond that period, all the days of her impure discharge she shall continue as though in her menstrual impurity; she is unclean.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Any bed on which she lies all the days of her discharge shall be to her like her bed at menstruation; and every thing on which she sits shall be unclean, like her uncleanness at that time.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Likewise, whoever touches them shall be unclean and shall wash his clothes and bathe in water and be unclean until evening.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When she becomes clean from her discharge, she shall count off for herself seven days; and afterward she will be clean.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then on the eighth day she shall take for herself two turtledoves or two young pigeons and bring them in to the priest, to the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The priest shall offer the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3199L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3199L\"></sup>one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. So the priest shall make atonement on her behalf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because of her impure discharge.’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Thus you shall keep the sons of Israel separated from their uncleanness, so that they will not die in their uncleanness by their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3200M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3200M\"></sup>defiling My tabernacle that is among them.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This is the law for the one with a discharge, and for the man who has a seminal emission so that he is unclean by it,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and for the woman who is ill because of menstrual impurity, and for the one who has a discharge, whether a male or a female, or a man who lies with an unclean woman."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3203A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3203A\"></sup>the death of the two sons of Aaron, when they had approached the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and died.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses:“Tell your brother Aaron that he shall not enter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3204B\"></sup>at any time into the holy place inside the veil, before the mercy seat which is on the ark, or he will die; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3204C\"></sup>I will appear in the cloud over the mercy seat.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Aaron shall enter the holy place with this: with a bull for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3205D\"></sup>sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall put on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3206E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3206E\"></sup>holy linen tunic, and the linen undergarments shall be next to his body, and he shall be girded with the linen sash and attired with the linen turban (these are holy garments). Then he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3206F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3206F\"></sup>bathe his body in water and put them on.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He shall take from the congregation of the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3207G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3207G\"></sup>two male goats for a sin offering and one ram for a burnt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3208H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3208H\"></sup>Aaron shall offer the bull for the sin offering which is for himself, that he may make atonement for himself and for his household.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He shall take the two goats and present them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Aaron shall cast lots for the two goats, one lot for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the other lot for the scapegoat.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Aaron shall offer the goat on which the lot for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell, and make it a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the goat on which the lot for the scapegoat fell shall be presented alive before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3212I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3212I\"></sup>atonement upon it, to send it into the wilderness as the scapegoat.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Then Aaron shall offer the bull of the sin offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3213J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3213J\"></sup>which is for himself and make atonement for himself and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3213K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3213K\"></sup>for his household, and he shall slaughter the bull of the sin offering which is for himself.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall take a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3214L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3214L\"></sup>firepan full of coals of fire from upon the altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and two handfuls of finely ground <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3214M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3214M\"></sup>sweet incense, and bring <i>it</i> inside the veil.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He shall put the incense on the fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the cloud of incense may cover the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3215N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3215N\"></sup>mercy seat that is on <i>the ark of</i> the testimony, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3215O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3215O\"></sup>otherwise he will die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3216P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3216P\"></sup>he shall take some of the blood of the bull and sprinkle <i>it</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3216Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3216Q\"></sup>with his finger on the mercy seat on the east <i>side</i>; also in front of the mercy seat he shall sprinkle some of the blood with his finger seven times.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Then he shall slaughter the goat of the sin offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3217R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3217R\"></sup>which is for the people, and bring its blood inside the veil and do with its blood as he did with the blood of the bull, and sprinkle it on the mercy seat and in front of the mercy seat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3218S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3218S\"></sup>He shall make atonement for the holy place, because of the impurities of the sons of Israel and because of their transgressions in regard to all their sins; and thus he shall do for the tent of meeting which abides with them in the midst of their impurities.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When he goes in to make atonement in the holy place, no one shall be in the tent of meeting until he comes out, that he may make atonement for himself and for his household and for all the assembly of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he shall go out to the altar that is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and make atonement for it, and shall take some of the blood of the bull and of the blood of the goat and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3220T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3220T\"></sup>put it on the horns of the altar on all sides.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3221U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3221U\"></sup>With his finger he shall sprinkle some of the blood on it seven times and cleanse it, and from the impurities of the sons of Israel consecrate it.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When he finishes atoning for the holy place and the tent of meeting and the altar, he shall offer the live goat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Aaron shall lay both of his hands on the head of the live goat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3223V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3223V\"></sup>confess over it all the iniquities of the sons of Israel and all their transgressions in regard to all their sins; and he shall lay them on the head of the goat and send <i>it</i> away into the wilderness by the hand of a man who <i>stands</i> in readiness.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The goat shall bear on itself all their iniquities to a solitary land; and he shall release the goat in the wilderness.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Then Aaron shall come into the tent of meeting and take off <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3225W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3225W\"></sup>the linen garments which he put on when he went into the holy place, and shall leave them there.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3226X\"></sup>He shall bathe his body with water in a holy place and put on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3226Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3226Y\"></sup>his clothes, and come forth and offer his burnt offering and the burnt offering of the people and make atonement for himself and for the people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he shall offer up in smoke the fat of the sin offering on the altar.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The one who released the goat as the scapegoat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3228Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3228Z\"></sup>shall wash his clothes and bathe his body with water; then afterward he shall come into the camp.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the bull of the sin offering and the goat of the sin offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3229AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3229AA\"></sup>whose blood was brought in to make atonement in the holy place, shall be taken outside the camp, and they shall burn their hides, their flesh, and their refuse in the fire.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3230AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3230AB\"></sup>one who burns them shall wash his clothes and bathe his body with water, then afterward he shall come into the camp.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<i>This</i> shall be a permanent statute for you: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3231AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3231AC\"></sup>in the seventh month, on the tenth day of the month, you shall humble your souls and not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3231AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3231AD\"></sup>do any work, whether the native, or the alien who sojourns among you;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>for it is on this day that atonement shall be made for you to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3232AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3232AE\"></sup>cleanse you; you will be clean from all your sins before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>It is to be a sabbath of solemn rest for you, that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3233AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3233AF\"></sup>humble your souls; it is a permanent statute.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So the priest who is anointed and ordained to serve as priest in his father’s place shall make atonement: he shall thus put on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3234AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3234AG\"></sup>the linen garments, the holy garments,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and make atonement for the holy sanctuary, and he shall make atonement for the tent of meeting and for the altar. He shall also make atonement for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3235AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3235AH\"></sup>the priests and for all the people of the assembly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now you shall have this as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3236AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3236AI\"></sup>permanent statute, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3236AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3236AJ\"></sup>make atonement for the sons of Israel for all their sins once every year.” And just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses, <i>so</i> he did."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and to his sons and to all the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded, saying,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Any man from the house of Israel who slaughters an ox or a lamb or a goat in the camp, or who slaughters it outside the camp,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3240A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3240A\"></sup>has not brought it to the doorway of the tent of meeting to present <i>it</i> as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, bloodguiltiness is to be reckoned to that man. He has shed blood and that man shall be cut off from among his people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The reason is so that the sons of Israel may bring their sacrifices which they were sacrificing in the open field, that they may bring them in to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, at the doorway of the tent of meeting to the priest, and sacrifice them as sacrifices of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priest shall sprinkle the blood on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the doorway of the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3242B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3242B\"></sup>offer up the fat in smoke as a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3243C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3243C\"></sup>They shall no longer sacrifice their sacrifices to the goat demons with which they play the harlot. This shall be a permanent statute to them throughout their generations.”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Then you shall say to them, ‘Any man from the house of Israel, or from the aliens who sojourn among them, who offers a burnt offering or sacrifice,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3245D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3245D\"></sup>does not bring it to the doorway of the tent of meeting to offer it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that man also shall be cut off from his people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3246E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3246E\"></sup>And any man from the house of Israel, or from the aliens who sojourn among them, who eats any blood, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3246F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3246F\"></sup>I will set My face against that person who eats blood and will cut him off from among his people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3247G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3247G\"></sup>the life of the flesh is in the blood, and I have given it to you on the altar to make atonement for your souls; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3247H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3247H\"></sup>it is the blood by reason of the life that makes atonement.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore I said to the sons of Israel, ‘No person among you may eat blood, nor may any alien who sojourns among you eat blood.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So when any man from the sons of Israel, or from the aliens who sojourn among them, in hunting catches a beast or a bird which may be eaten, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3249I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3249I\"></sup>he shall pour out its blood and cover it with earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3250J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3250J\"></sup>For <i>as for the</i> life of all flesh, its blood is <i>identified</i> with its life. Therefore I said to the sons of Israel, ‘You are not to eat the blood of any flesh, for the life of all flesh is its blood; whoever eats it shall be cut off.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3251K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3251K\"></sup>When any person eats <i>an animal</i> which dies or is torn <i>by beasts</i>, whether he is a native or an alien, he shall wash his clothes and bathe in water, and remain unclean until evening; then he will become clean.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if he does not wash <i>them</i> or bathe his body, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3252L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3252L\"></sup>he shall bear his guilt.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3254A\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall not do what is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3255B\"></sup>done in the land of Egypt where you lived, nor are you to do what is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3255C\"></sup>done in the land of Canaan where I am bringing you; you shall not walk in their statutes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You are to perform My judgments and keep My statutes, to live in accord with them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3256D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3256D\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So you shall keep My statutes and My judgments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3257E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3257E\"></sup>by which a man may live if he does them; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>‘None of you shall approach any blood relative of his to uncover nakedness; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3259F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3259F\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father, that is, the nakedness of your mother. She is your mother; you are not to uncover her nakedness.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3260G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3260G\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father’s wife; it is your father’s nakedness.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3261H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3261H\"></sup>The nakedness of your sister, <i>either</i> your father’s daughter or your mother’s daughter, whether born at home or born outside, their nakedness you shall not uncover.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The nakedness of your son’s daughter or your daughter’s daughter, their nakedness you shall not uncover; for their nakedness is yours.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The nakedness of your father’s wife’s daughter, born to your father, she is your sister, you shall not uncover her nakedness.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3264I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3264I\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father’s sister; she is your father’s blood relative.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your mother’s sister, for she is your mother’s blood relative.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3266J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3266J\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your father’s brother; you shall not approach his wife, she is your aunt.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3267K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3267K\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your daughter-in-law; she is your son’s wife, you shall not uncover her nakedness.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3268L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3268L\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of your brother’s wife; it is your brother’s nakedness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3269M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3269M\"></sup>You shall not uncover the nakedness of a woman and of her daughter, nor shall you take her son’s daughter or her daughter’s daughter, to uncover her nakedness; they are blood relatives. It is lewdness.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall not marry a woman in addition to her sister as a rival while she is alive, to uncover her nakedness.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3271N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3271N\"></sup>Also you shall not approach a woman to uncover her nakedness during her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3271O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3271O\"></sup>menstrual impurity.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3272P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3272P\"></sup>You shall not have intercourse with your neighbor’s wife, to be defiled with her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You shall not give any of your offspring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3273Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3273Q\"></sup>to offer them to Molech, nor shall you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3273R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3273R\"></sup>profane the name of your God; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3274S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3274S\"></sup>You shall not lie with a male as one lies with a female; it is an abomination.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3275T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3275T\"></sup>Also you shall not have intercourse with any animal to be defiled with it, nor shall any woman stand before an animal to mate with it; it is a perversion.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘Do not defile yourselves by any of these things; for by all these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3276U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3276U\"></sup>the nations which I am casting out before you have become defiled.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For the land has become defiled, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3277V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3277V\"></sup>therefore I have brought its punishment upon it, so the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3277W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3277W\"></sup>has spewed out its inhabitants.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But as for you, you are to keep My statutes and My judgments and shall not do any of these abominations, <i>neither</i> the native, nor the alien who sojourns among you",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>(for the men of the land who have been before you have done all these abominations, and the land has become defiled);",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>so that the land will not spew you out, should you defile it, as it has spewed out the nation which has been before you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For whoever does any of these abominations, those persons who do <i>so</i> shall be cut off from among their people.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Thus you are to keep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3282X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3282X\"></sup>My charge, that you do not practice any of the abominable customs which have been practiced before you, so as not to defile yourselves with them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3282Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3282Y\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to all the congregation of the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3284A\"></sup>You shall be holy, for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God am holy.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Every one of you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3285B\"></sup>shall reverence his mother and his father, and you shall keep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3285C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3285C\"></sup>My sabbaths; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3285D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3285D\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Do not turn to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3286E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3286E\"></sup>idols or make for yourselves molten <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3286F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3286F\"></sup>gods; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘Now when you offer a sacrifice of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall offer it so that you may be accepted.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It shall be eaten the same day you offer <i>it</i>, and the next day; but what remains until the third day shall be burned with fire.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So if it is eaten at all on the third day, it is an offense; it will not be accepted.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Everyone who eats it will bear his iniquity, for he has profaned the holy thing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and that person shall be cut off from his people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3291G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3291G\"></sup>Now when you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not reap to the very corners of your field, nor shall you gather the gleanings of your harvest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Nor shall you glean your vineyard, nor shall you gather the fallen fruit of your vineyard; you shall leave them for the needy and for the stranger. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3293H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3293H\"></sup>You shall not steal, nor deal falsely, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3293I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3293I\"></sup>nor lie to one another.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3294J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3294J\"></sup>You shall not swear falsely by My name, so as to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3294K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3294K\"></sup>profane the name of your God; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3295L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3295L\"></sup>You shall not oppress your neighbor, nor rob <i>him</i>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3295M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3295M\"></sup>The wages of a hired man are not to remain with you all night until morning.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall not curse a deaf man, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3296N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3296N\"></sup>place a stumbling block before the blind, but you shall revere your God; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3297O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3297O\"></sup>You shall do no injustice in judgment; you shall not be partial to the poor nor defer to the great, but you are to judge your neighbor fairly.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall not go about as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3298P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3298P\"></sup>a slanderer among your people, and you are not to act against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3298Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3298Q\"></sup>life of your neighbor; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3299R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3299R\"></sup>shall not hate your fellow countryman in your heart; you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3299S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3299S\"></sup>may surely reprove your neighbor, but shall not incur sin because of him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3300T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3300T\"></sup>You shall not take vengeance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3300U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3300U\"></sup>nor bear any grudge against the sons of your people, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3300V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3300V\"></sup>you shall love your neighbor as yourself; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>‘You are to keep My statutes. You shall not breed together two kinds of your cattle; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3301W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3301W\"></sup>you shall not sow your field with two kinds of seed, nor wear a garment upon you of two kinds of material mixed together.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3302X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3302X\"></sup>Now if a man lies carnally with a woman who is a slave acquired for <i>another</i> man, but who has in no way been redeemed nor given her freedom, there shall be punishment; they shall not, <i>however</i>, be put to death, because she was not free.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He shall bring his guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the doorway of the tent of meeting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3303Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3303Y\"></sup>a ram for a guilt offering.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The priest shall also make atonement for him with the ram of the guilt offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his sin which he has committed, and the sin which he has committed will be forgiven him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘When you enter the land and plant all kinds of trees for food, then you shall count their fruit as forbidden. Three years it shall be forbidden to you; <i>it</i> shall not be eaten.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But in the fourth year all its fruit shall be holy, an offering of praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In the fifth year you are to eat of its fruit, that its yield may increase for you; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘You shall not eat <i>anything</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3308Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3308Z\"></sup>with the blood, nor practice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3308AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3308AA\"></sup>divination or soothsaying.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3309AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3309AB\"></sup>You shall not round off the side-growth of your heads nor harm the edges of your beard.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You shall not make any cuts in your body for the dead nor make any tattoo marks on yourselves: I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3311AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3311AC\"></sup>Do not profane your daughter by making her a harlot, so that the land will not fall to harlotry and the land become full of lewdness.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3312AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3312AD\"></sup>keep My sabbaths and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3312AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3312AE\"></sup>revere My sanctuary; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>‘Do not turn to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3313AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3313AF\"></sup>mediums or spiritists; do not seek them out to be defiled by them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3314AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3314AG\"></sup>You shall rise up before the grayheaded and honor the aged, and you shall revere your God; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3315AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3315AH\"></sup>When a stranger resides with you in your land, you shall not do him wrong.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The stranger who resides with you shall be to you as the native among you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3316AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3316AI\"></sup>you shall love him as yourself, for you were aliens in the land of Egypt; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3317AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3317AJ\"></sup>You shall do no wrong in judgment, in measurement of weight, or capacity.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You shall have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3318AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3318AK\"></sup>just balances, just weights, a just ephah, and a just hin; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out from the land of Egypt.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You shall thus observe all My statutes and all My ordinances and do them; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“You shall also say to the sons of Israel:‘Any man from the sons of Israel or from the aliens sojourning in Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3321A\"></sup>who gives any of his offspring to Molech, shall surely be put to death; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3321B\"></sup>the people of the land shall stone him with stones.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will also set My face against that man and will cut him off from among his people, because he has given some of his offspring to Molech, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3322C\"></sup>so as to defile My sanctuary and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3322D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3322D\"></sup>to profane My holy name.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the people of the land, however, should ever disregard that man when he gives any of his offspring to Molech, so as not to put him to death,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>then I Myself will set My face against that man and against his family, and I will cut off from among their people both him and all those who play the harlot after him, by playing the harlot after Molech.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>‘As for the person who turns to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3325E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3325E\"></sup>mediums and to spiritists, to play the harlot after them, I will also set My face against that person and will cut him off from among his people.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall consecrate yourselves therefore and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3326F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3326F\"></sup>be holy, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3327G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3327G\"></sup>You shall keep My statutes and practice them; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3328H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3328H\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> anyone who curses his father or his mother, he shall surely be put to death; he has cursed his father or his mother, his bloodguiltiness is upon him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3329I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3329I\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who commits adultery with another man’s wife, one who commits adultery with his friend’s wife, the adulterer and the adulteress shall surely be put to death.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3330J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3330J\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with his father’s wife, he has uncovered his father’s nakedness; both of them shall surely be put to death, their bloodguiltiness is upon them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3331K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3331K\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with his daughter-in-law, both of them shall surely be put to death; they have committed incest, their bloodguiltiness is upon them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3332L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3332L\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with a male as those who lie with a woman, both of them have committed a detestable act; they shall surely be put to death. Their bloodguiltiness is upon them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3333M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3333M\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who marries a woman and her mother, it is immorality; both he and they shall be burned with fire, so that there will be no immorality in your midst.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3334N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3334N\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with an animal, he shall surely be put to death; you shall also kill the animal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If <i>there is</i> a woman who approaches any animal to mate with it, you shall kill the woman and the animal; they shall surely be put to death. Their bloodguiltiness is upon them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3336O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3336O\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who takes his sister, his father’s daughter or his mother’s daughter, so that he sees her nakedness and she sees his nakedness, it is a disgrace; and they shall be cut off in the sight of the sons of their people. He has uncovered his sister’s nakedness; he bears his guilt.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3337P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3337P\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with a menstruous woman and uncovers her nakedness, he has laid bare her flow, and she has exposed the flow of her blood; thus both of them shall be cut off from among their people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3338Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3338Q\"></sup>You shall also not uncover the nakedness of your mother’s sister or of your father’s sister, for such a one has made naked his blood relative; they will bear their guilt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3339R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3339R\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who lies with his uncle’s wife he has uncovered his uncle’s nakedness; they will bear their sin. They will die childless.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3340S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3340S\"></sup>If <i>there is</i> a man who takes his brother’s wife, it is abhorrent; he has uncovered his brother’s nakedness. They will be childless.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>‘You are therefore to keep all My statutes and all My ordinances and do them, so that the land to which I am bringing you to live will not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3341T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3341T\"></sup>spew you out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moreover, you shall not follow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3342U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3342U\"></sup>the customs of the nation which I will drive out before you, for they did all these things, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3342V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3342V\"></sup>therefore I have abhorred them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hence I have said to you, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3343W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3343W\"></sup>You are to possess their land, and I Myself will give it to you to possess it, a land flowing with milk and honey.” I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3343X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3343X\"></sup>separated you from the peoples.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3344Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3344Y\"></sup>You are therefore to make a distinction between the clean animal and the unclean, and between the unclean bird and the clean; and you shall not make yourselves detestable by animal or by bird or by anything that creeps on the ground, which I have separated for you as unclean.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Thus you are to be holy to Me, for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> am holy; and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3345Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3345Z\"></sup>have set you apart from the peoples to be Mine.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘Now a man or a woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3346AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3346AA\"></sup>who is a medium or a spiritist shall surely be put to death. They shall be stoned with stones, their bloodguiltiness is upon them.’”"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Speak to the priests, the sons of Aaron, and say to them:‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3347A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3347A\"></sup>No one shall defile himself for a <i>dead</i> person among his people,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3348B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3348B\"></sup>except for his relatives who are nearest to him, his mother and his father and his son and his daughter and his brother,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>also for his virgin sister, who is near to him because she has had no husband; for her he may defile himself.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall not defile himself as a relative by marriage among his people, and so profane himself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3351C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3351C\"></sup>They shall not make any baldness on their heads, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3351D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3351D\"></sup>nor shave off the edges of their beards, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3351E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3351E\"></sup>nor make any cuts in their flesh.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They shall be holy to their God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3352F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3352F\"></sup>not profane the name of their God, for they present the offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3352G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3352G\"></sup>the food of their God; so they shall be holy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3353H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3353H\"></sup>They shall not take a woman who is profaned by harlotry, nor shall they take a woman divorced from her husband; for he is holy to his God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall consecrate him, therefore, for he offers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3354I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3354I\"></sup>the food of your God; he shall be holy to you; for I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who sanctifies you, am holy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3355J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3355J\"></sup>Also the daughter of any priest, if she profanes herself by harlotry, she profanes her father; she shall be burned with fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘The priest who is the highest among his brothers, on whose head the anointing oil has been poured and who has been consecrated to wear the garments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3356K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3356K\"></sup>shall not uncover his head nor tear his clothes;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3357L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3357L\"></sup>nor shall he approach any dead person, nor defile himself <i>even</i> for his father or his mother;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3358M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3358M\"></sup>nor shall he go out of the sanctuary nor profane the sanctuary of his God, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3358N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3358N\"></sup>the consecration of the anointing oil of his God is on him; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He shall take a wife in her virginity.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3360O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3360O\"></sup>A widow, or a divorced woman, or one who is profaned by harlotry, these he may not take; but rather he is to marry a virgin of his own people,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>so that he will not profane his offspring among his people; for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies him.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Speak to Aaron, saying, ‘No man of your offspring throughout their generations who has a defect shall approach to offer the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3363P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3363P\"></sup>food of his God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3364Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3364Q\"></sup>For no one who has a defect shall approach: a blind man, or a lame man, or he who has a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3364R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3364R\"></sup>disfigured <i>face</i>, or any deformed <i>limb</i>,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>or a man who has a broken foot or broken hand,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>or a hunchback or a dwarf, or <i>one who has</i> a defect in his eye or eczema or scabs or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3366S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3366S\"></sup>crushed testicles.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>No man among the descendants of Aaron the priest who has a defect is to come near to offer the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> offerings by fire; <i>since</i> he has a defect, he shall not come near to offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3367T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3367T\"></sup>the food of his God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He may eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3368U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3368U\"></sup>the food of his God, <i>both</i> of the most holy and of the holy,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>only he shall not go in to the veil or come near the altar because he has a defect, so that he will not profane My sanctuaries. For I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses spoke to Aaron and to his sons and to all the sons of Israel."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell Aaron and his sons to be careful with the holy <i>gifts</i> of the sons of Israel, which they dedicate to Me, so as not to profane My holy name; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3373A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3373A\"></sup>If any man among all your descendants throughout your generations approaches the holy <i>gifts</i> which the sons of Israel dedicate to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, while he has an uncleanness, that person shall be cut off from before Me; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3374B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3374B\"></sup>No man of the descendants of Aaron, who is a leper or who has a discharge, may eat of the holy <i>gifts</i> until he is clean. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3374C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3374C\"></sup>And if one touches anything made unclean by a corpse or if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3374D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3374D\"></sup>a man has a seminal emission,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3375E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3375E\"></sup>if a man touches any teeming things by which he is made unclean, or any man by whom he is made unclean, whatever his uncleanness;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>a person who touches any such shall be unclean until evening, and shall not eat of the holy <i>gifts</i> unless he has bathed his body in water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But when the sun sets, he will be clean, and afterward he shall eat of the holy <i>gifts</i>, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3377F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3377F\"></sup>it is his food.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He shall not eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3378G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3378G\"></sup><i>an animal</i> which dies or is torn <i>by beasts</i>, becoming unclean by it; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They shall therefore keep <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3379H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3379H\"></sup>My charge, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3379I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3379I\"></sup>they will not bear sin because of it and die thereby because they profane it; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3380J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3380J\"></sup>No layman, however, is to eat the holy <i>gift</i>; a sojourner with the priest or a hired man shall not eat of the holy <i>gift</i>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3381K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3381K\"></sup>But if a priest buys a slave as <i>his</i> property with his money, that one may eat of it, and those who are born in his house may eat of his food.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If a priest’s daughter is married to a layman, she shall not eat of the offering of the <i>gifts</i>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if a priest’s daughter becomes a widow or divorced, and has no child and returns to her father’s house as in her youth, she shall eat of her father’s food; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3383L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3383L\"></sup>but no layman shall eat of it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3384M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3384M\"></sup>But if a man eats a holy <i>gift</i> unintentionally, then he shall add to it a fifth of it and shall give the holy <i>gift</i> to the priest.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3385N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3385N\"></sup>They shall not profane the holy <i>gifts</i> of the sons of Israel which they offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and <i>so</i> cause them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3386O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3386O\"></sup>to bear punishment for guilt by eating their holy <i>gifts</i>; for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies them.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and to his sons and to all the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3388P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3388P\"></sup>Any man of the house of Israel or of the aliens in Israel who presents his offering, whether it is any of their votive or any of their freewill offerings, which they present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for a burnt offering—",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3389Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3389Q\"></sup>for you to be accepted—<i>it must be</i> a male without defect from the cattle, the sheep, or the goats.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3390R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3390R\"></sup>Whatever has a defect, you shall not offer, for it will not be accepted for you.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When a man offers a sacrifice of peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3391S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3391S\"></sup>to fulfill a special vow or for a freewill offering, of the herd or of the flock, it must be perfect to be accepted; there shall be no defect in it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Those <i>that are</i> blind or fractured or maimed or having a running sore or eczema or scabs, you shall not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, nor make of them an offering by fire on the altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In respect to an ox or a lamb which has an overgrown or stunted <i>member</i>, you may present it for a freewill offering, but for a vow it will not be accepted.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3394T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3394T\"></sup>anything <i>with its testicles</i> bruised or crushed or torn or cut, you shall not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, or sacrifice in your land,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>nor shall you accept any such from the hand of a foreigner for offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3395U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3395U\"></sup>as the food of your God; for their corruption is in them, they have a defect, they shall not be accepted for you.’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“When an ox or a sheep or a goat is born, it shall remain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3397V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3397V\"></sup>seven days with its mother, and from the eighth day on it shall be accepted as a sacrifice of an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3398W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3398W\"></sup>But, <i>whether</i> it is an ox or a sheep, you shall not kill <i>both</i> it and its young in one day.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When you sacrifice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3399X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3399X\"></sup>a sacrifice of thanksgiving to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you shall sacrifice it so that you may be accepted.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It shall be eaten on the same day, you shall leave none of it until morning; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3401Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3401Y\"></sup>So you shall keep My commandments, and do them; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“You shall not profane My holy name, but I will be sanctified among the sons of Israel; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies you,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3403Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3403Z\"></sup>who brought you out from the land of Egypt, to be your God; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke again to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3405A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3405A\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> appointed times which you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3405B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3405B\"></sup>proclaim as holy convocations—My appointed times are these:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3406C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3406C\"></sup>For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day there is a sabbath of complete rest, a holy convocation. You shall not do any work; it is a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in all your dwellings.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘These are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3407D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3407D\"></sup>appointed times of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, holy convocations which you shall proclaim at the times appointed for them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3408E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3408E\"></sup>In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at twilight is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> Passover.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then on the fifteenth day of the same month there is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3409F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3409F\"></sup>Feast of Unleavened Bread to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for seven days you shall eat unleavened bread.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>On the first day you shall have a holy convocation; you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3410G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3410G\"></sup>not do any laborious work.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But for seven days you shall present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. On the seventh day is a holy convocation; you shall not do any laborious work.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘When you enter the land which I am going to give to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3413H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3413H\"></sup>reap its harvest, then you shall bring in the sheaf of the first fruits of your harvest to the priest.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He shall wave the sheaf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for you to be accepted; on the day after the sabbath the priest shall wave it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now on the day when you wave the sheaf, you shall offer a male lamb one year old without defect for a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3416I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3416I\"></sup>grain offering shall then be two-tenths <i>of an ephah</i> of fine flour mixed with oil, an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>for</i> a soothing aroma, with its drink offering, a fourth of a hin of wine.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Until this same day, until you have brought in the offering of your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3417J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3417J\"></sup>you shall eat neither bread nor roasted grain nor new growth. It is to be a perpetual statute throughout your generations in all your dwelling places.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3418K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3418K\"></sup>You shall also count for yourselves from the day after the sabbath, from the day when you brought in the sheaf of the wave offering; there shall be seven complete sabbaths.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall count fifty days to the day after the seventh sabbath; then you shall present a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3419L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3419L\"></sup>new grain offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall bring in from your dwelling places two <i>loaves</i> of bread for a wave offering, made of two-tenths <i>of an</i> <i>ephah</i>; they shall be of a fine flour, baked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3420M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3420M\"></sup>with leaven as first fruits to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Along with the bread you shall present seven one year old male lambs without defect, and a bull of the herd and two rams; they are to be a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with their grain offering and their drink offerings, an offering by fire of a soothing aroma to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You shall also offer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3422N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3422N\"></sup>one male goat for a sin offering and two male lambs one year old for a sacrifice of peace offerings.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priest shall then wave them with the bread of the first fruits for a wave offering with two lambs before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they are to be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>On this same day you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3424O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3424O\"></sup>make a proclamation as well; you are to have a holy convocation. You shall do no laborious <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3424P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3424P\"></sup>work. It is to be a perpetual statute in all your dwelling places throughout your generations.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3425Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3425Q\"></sup>When you reap the harvest of your land, moreover, you shall not reap to the very corners of your field nor gather the gleaning of your harvest; you are to leave them for the needy and the alien. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Again the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3427R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3427R\"></sup>In the seventh month on the first of the month you shall have a rest, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3427S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3427S\"></sup>reminder by blowing <i>of trumpets</i>, a holy convocation.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3428T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3428T\"></sup>not do any laborious work, but you shall present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“On exactly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3430U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3430U\"></sup>the tenth day of this seventh month is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3430V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3430V\"></sup>the day of atonement; it shall be a holy convocation for you, and you shall humble your souls and present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You shall not do any work on this same day, for it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3431W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3431W\"></sup>day of atonement, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3431X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3431X\"></sup>to make atonement on your behalf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If there is any person who will not humble himself on this same day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3432Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3432Y\"></sup>he shall be cut off from his people.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As for any person who does any work on this same day, that person I will destroy from among his people.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>You shall do no work at all. It is to be a perpetual statute throughout your generations in all your dwelling places.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It is to be a sabbath of complete rest to you, and you shall humble your souls; on the ninth of the month at evening, from evening until evening you shall keep your sabbath.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Again the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘On <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3437Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3437Z\"></sup>the fifteenth of this seventh month is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3437AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3437AA\"></sup>Feast of Booths for seven days to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>On the first day is a holy convocation; you shall do <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3438AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3438AB\"></sup>no laborious work of any kind.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3439AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3439AC\"></sup>For seven days you shall present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. On <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3439AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3439AD\"></sup>the eighth day you shall have a holy convocation and present an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is an assembly. You shall do no laborious work.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>‘These are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3440AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3440AE\"></sup>the appointed times of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which you shall proclaim as holy convocations, to present offerings by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—burnt offerings and grain offerings, sacrifices and drink offerings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3440AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3440AF\"></sup><i>each</i> day’s matter on its own day—",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>besides <i>those of</i> the sabbaths of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and besides your gifts and besides all your votive and freewill offerings, which you give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>‘On exactly the fifteenth day of the seventh month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3442AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3442AG\"></sup>when you have gathered in the crops of the land, you shall celebrate the feast of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days, with a rest on the first day and a rest on the eighth day.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now on the first day you shall take for yourselves the foliage of beautiful trees, palm branches and boughs of leafy trees and willows of the brook, and you shall rejoice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for seven days.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You shall thus celebrate it <i>as</i> a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days in the year. It <i>shall be</i> a perpetual statute throughout your generations; you shall celebrate it in the seventh month.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>You shall live <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3445AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3445AH\"></sup>in booths for seven days; all the native-born in Israel shall live in booths,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3446AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3446AI\"></sup>your generations may know that I had the sons of Israel live in booths when I brought them out from the land of Egypt. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So Moses declared to the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3447AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3447AJ\"></sup>the appointed times of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the sons of Israel that they bring to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3449A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3449A\"></sup>clear oil from beaten olives for the light, to make a lamp burn continually.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Outside the veil of testimony in the tent of meeting, Aaron shall keep it in order from evening to morning before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually; <i>it shall be</i> a perpetual statute throughout your generations.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He shall keep the lamps in order on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3451B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3451B\"></sup>pure <i>gold</i> lampstand before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3452C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3452C\"></sup>Then you shall take fine flour and bake twelve cakes with it; two-tenths <i>of an ephah</i> shall be <i>in</i> each cake.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall set them <i>in</i> two rows, six <i>to</i> a row, on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3453D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3453D\"></sup>pure <i>gold</i> table before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall put pure frankincense on each row that it may be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3454E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3454E\"></sup>a memorial portion for the bread, <i>even</i> an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3455F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3455F\"></sup>Every sabbath day he shall set it in order before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3455G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3455G\"></sup>continually; it is an everlasting covenant for the sons of Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3456H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3456H\"></sup>It shall be for Aaron and his sons, and they shall eat it in a holy place; for it is most holy to him from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> offerings by fire, <i>his</i> portion forever.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the son of an Israelite woman, whose father was an Egyptian, went out among the sons of Israel; and the Israelite woman’s son and a man of Israel struggled with each other in the camp.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The son of the Israelite woman blasphemed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3458I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3458I\"></sup>Name and cursed. So they brought him to Moses. (Now his mother’s name was Shelomith, the daughter of Dibri, of the tribe of Dan.)",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They put him in custody so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3459J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3459J\"></sup>the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> might be made clear to them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Bring the one who has cursed outside the camp, and let all who heard him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3461K\"></sup>lay their hands on his head; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3461L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3461L\"></sup>let all the congregation stone him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You shall speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3462M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3462M\"></sup>If anyone curses his God, then he will bear his sin.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Moreover, the one who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3463N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3463N\"></sup>blasphemes the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall surely be put to death; all the congregation shall certainly stone him. The alien as well as the native, when he blasphemes the Name, shall be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3464O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3464O\"></sup>If a man takes the life of any human being, he shall surely be put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3465P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3465P\"></sup>The one who takes the life of an animal shall make it good, life for life.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If a man injures his neighbor, just as he has done, so it shall be done to him:",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3467Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3467Q\"></sup>fracture for fracture, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3467R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3467R\"></sup>eye for eye, tooth for tooth; just as he has injured a man, so it shall be inflicted on him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Thus the one who kills an animal shall make it good, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3468S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3468S\"></sup>the one who kills a man shall be put to death.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>There shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3469T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3469T\"></sup>one standard for you; it shall be for the stranger as well as the native, for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Moses spoke to the sons of Israel, and they brought the one who had cursed outside the camp and stoned him with stones. Thus the sons of Israel did, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> then spoke to Moses at Mount Sinai, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘When you come into the land which I shall give you, then the land shall have a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3473A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3473A\"></sup>Six years you shall sow your field, and six years you shall prune your vineyard and gather in its crop,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but during <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3474B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3474B\"></sup>the seventh year the land shall have a sabbath rest, a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; you shall not sow your field nor prune your vineyard.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your harvest’s aftergrowth you shall not reap, and your grapes of untrimmed vines you shall not gather; the land shall have a sabbatical year.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3476C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3476C\"></sup>All of you shall have the sabbath <i>products</i> of the land for food; yourself, and your male and female slaves, and your hired man and your foreign resident, those who live as aliens with you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Even your cattle and the animals that are in your land shall have all its crops to eat.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>‘You are also to count off seven sabbaths of years for yourself, seven times seven years, so that you have the time of the seven sabbaths of years, <i>namely</i>, forty-nine years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall then sound a ram’s horn abroad on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3479D\"></sup>the tenth day of the seventh month; on the day of atonement you shall sound a horn all through your land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall thus consecrate the fiftieth year and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3480E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3480E\"></sup>proclaim a release through the land to all its inhabitants. It shall be a jubilee for you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3480F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3480F\"></sup>each of you shall return to his own property, and each of you shall return to his family.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall have the fiftieth year as a jubilee; you shall not sow, nor reap its aftergrowth, nor gather in <i>from</i> its untrimmed vines.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For it is a jubilee; it shall be holy to you. You shall eat its crops out of the field.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3483G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3483G\"></sup>On this year of jubilee each of you shall return to his own property.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>If you make a sale, moreover, to your friend or buy from your friend’s hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3484H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3484H\"></sup>you shall not wrong one another.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Corresponding to the number of years after the jubilee, you shall buy from your friend; he is to sell to you according to the number of years of crops.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3486I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3486I\"></sup>In proportion to the extent of the years you shall increase its price, and in proportion to the fewness of the years you shall diminish its price, for <i>it is</i> a number of crops he is selling to you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3487J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3487J\"></sup>you shall not wrong one another, but you shall fear your God; for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>‘You shall thus observe My statutes and keep My judgments, so as to carry them out, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3488K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3488K\"></sup>you may live securely on the land.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the land will yield its produce, so that you can eat your fill and live securely on it.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if you say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3490L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3490L\"></sup>What are we going to eat on the seventh year if we do not sow or gather in our crops?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3491M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3491M\"></sup>I will so order My blessing for you in the sixth year that it will bring forth the crop for three years.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When you are sowing the eighth year, you can still eat <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3492N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3492N\"></sup>old things from the crop, eating <i>the old</i> until the ninth year when its crop comes in.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘The land, moreover, shall not be sold permanently, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3493O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3493O\"></sup>the land is Mine; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3493P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3493P\"></sup>you are <i>but</i> aliens and sojourners with Me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Thus for every piece of your property, you are to provide for the redemption of the land.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3495Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3495Q\"></sup>If a fellow countryman of yours becomes so poor he has to sell part of his property, then his nearest kinsman is to come and buy back what his relative has sold.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Or in case a man has no kinsman, but so recovers his means as to find sufficient for its redemption,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3497R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3497R\"></sup>then he shall calculate the years since its sale and refund the balance to the man to whom he sold it, and so return to his property.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if he has not found sufficient means to get it back for himself, then what he has sold shall remain in the hands of its purchaser until the year of jubilee; but at the jubilee it shall revert, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3498S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3498S\"></sup>he may return to his property.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>‘Likewise, if a man sells a dwelling house in a walled city, then his redemption right remains valid until a full year from its sale; his right of redemption lasts a full year.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But if it is not bought back for him within the space of a full year, then the house that is in the walled city passes permanently to its purchaser throughout his generations; it does not revert in the jubilee.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The houses of the villages, however, which have no surrounding wall shall be considered as open fields; they have redemption rights and revert in the jubilee.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>As for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3502T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3502T\"></sup>cities of the Levites, the Levites have a permanent right of redemption for the houses of the cities which are their possession.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>What, therefore, belongs to the Levites may be redeemed and a house sale in the city of this possession reverts in the jubilee, for the houses of the cities of the Levites are their possession among the sons of Israel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3504U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3504U\"></sup>But pasture fields of their cities shall not be sold, for that is their perpetual possession.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3505V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3505V\"></sup>Now in case a countryman of yours becomes poor and his means with regard to you falter, then you are to sustain him, like a stranger or a sojourner, that he may live with you.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3506W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3506W\"></sup>Do not take usurious interest from him, but revere your God, that your countryman may live with you.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You shall not give him your silver at interest, nor your food for gain.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3508X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3508X\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt to give you the land of Canaan <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3508Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3508Y\"></sup>to be your God.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3509Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3509Z\"></sup>If a countryman of yours becomes so poor with regard to you that he sells himself to you, you shall not subject him to a slave’s service.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>He shall be with you as a hired man, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3510AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3510AA\"></sup>if he were a sojourner; he shall serve with you until the year of jubilee.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He shall then go out from you, he and his sons with him, and shall go back to his family, that he may return to the property of his forefathers.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>For they are My servants whom I brought out from the land of Egypt; they are not to be sold <i>in</i> a slave sale.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3513AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3513AB\"></sup>You shall not rule over him with severity, but are to revere your God.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>As for your male and female slaves whom you may have—you may acquire male and female slaves from the pagan nations that are around you.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then, too, <i>it is</i> out of the sons of the sojourners who live as aliens among you that you may gain acquisition, and out of their families who are with you, whom they will have produced in your land; they also may become your possession.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>You may even bequeath them to your sons after you, to receive as a possession; you can use them as permanent slaves. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3516AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3516AC\"></sup>But in respect to your countrymen, the sons of Israel, you shall not rule with severity over one another.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>‘Now if the means of a stranger or of a sojourner with you becomes sufficient, and a countryman of yours becomes so poor with regard to him as to sell himself to a stranger who is sojourning with you, or to the descendants of a stranger’s family,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>then he shall have redemption right after he has been sold. One of his brothers may redeem him,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>or his uncle, or his uncle’s son, may redeem him, or one of his blood relatives from his family may redeem him; or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3519AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3519AD\"></sup>if he prospers, he may redeem himself.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>He then with his purchaser shall calculate from the year when he sold himself to him up to the year of jubilee; and the price of his sale shall correspond to the number of years. <i>It is</i> like the days of a hired man <i>that</i> he shall be with him.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>If there are still many years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3521AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3521AE\"></sup>he shall refund part of his purchase price in proportion to them for his own redemption;",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>and if few years remain until the year of jubilee, he shall so calculate with him. In proportion to his years he is to refund <i>the amount for</i> his redemption.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Like a man hired year by year he shall be with him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3523AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3523AF\"></sup>he shall not rule over him with severity in your sight.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Even if he is not redeemed by these <i>means</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3524AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3524AG\"></sup>he shall still go out in the year of jubilee, he and his sons with him.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>For the sons of Israel are My servants; they are My servants whom I brought out from the land of Egypt. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>‘You shall not make for yourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3526A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3526A\"></sup>idols, nor shall you set up for yourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3526B\"></sup>an image or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3526C\"></sup>a <i>sacred</i> pillar, nor shall you place a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3526D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3526D\"></sup>figured stone in your land to bow down to it; for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3527E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3527E\"></sup>You shall keep My sabbaths and reverence My sanctuary; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3528F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3528F\"></sup>If you walk in My statutes and keep My commandments so as to carry them out,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3529G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3529G\"></sup>I shall give you rains in their season, so that the land will yield its produce and the trees of the field will bear their fruit.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3530H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3530H\"></sup>Indeed, your threshing will last for you until grape gathering, and grape gathering will last until sowing time. You will thus eat your food to the full and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3530I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3530I\"></sup>live securely in your land.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3531J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3531J\"></sup>I shall also grant peace in the land, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3531K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3531K\"></sup>you may lie down with no one making <i>you</i> tremble. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3531L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3531L\"></sup>I shall also eliminate harmful beasts from the land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3531M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3531M\"></sup>no sword will pass through your land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But you will chase your enemies and they will fall before you by the sword;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3533N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3533N\"></sup>five of you will chase a hundred, and a hundred of you will chase ten thousand, and your enemies will fall before you by the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So I will turn toward you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3534O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3534O\"></sup>make you fruitful and multiply you, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3534P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3534P\"></sup>confirm My covenant with you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3535Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3535Q\"></sup>You will eat the old supply and clear out the old because of the new.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3536R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3536R\"></sup>Moreover, I will make My dwelling among you, and My soul will not reject you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3537S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3537S\"></sup>I will also walk among you and be your God, and you shall be My people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3538T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3538T\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt so that <i>you</i> would not be their slaves, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3538U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3538U\"></sup>I broke the bars of your yoke and made you walk erect.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3539V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3539V\"></sup>But if you do not obey Me and do not carry out all these commandments,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>if, instead, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3540W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3540W\"></sup>reject My statutes, and if your soul abhors My ordinances so as not to carry out all My commandments, <i>and</i> so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3540X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3540X\"></sup>break My covenant,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I, in turn, will do this to you: I will appoint over you a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3541Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3541Y\"></sup>sudden terror, consumption and fever that will waste away the eyes and cause the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3541Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3541Z\"></sup>soul to pine away; also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3541AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3541AA\"></sup>you will sow your seed uselessly, for your enemies will eat it up.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will set My face against you so that you will be struck down before your enemies; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3542AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3542AB\"></sup>those who hate you will rule over you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3542AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3542AC\"></sup>you will flee when no one is pursuing you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If also after these things you do not obey Me, then I will punish you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3543AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3543AD\"></sup>seven times more for your sins.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I will also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3544AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3544AE\"></sup>break down your pride of power; I will also make your sky like iron and your earth like bronze.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3545AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3545AF\"></sup>Your strength will be spent uselessly, for your land will not yield its produce and the trees of the land will not yield their fruit.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>‘If then, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3546AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3546AG\"></sup>act with hostility against Me and are unwilling to obey Me, I will increase the plague on you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3546AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3546AH\"></sup>seven times according to your sins.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3547AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3547AI\"></sup>I will let loose among you the beasts of the field, which will bereave you of your children and destroy your cattle and reduce your number so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3547AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3547AJ\"></sup>your roads lie deserted.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3548AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3548AK\"></sup>And if by these things you are not turned to Me, but act with hostility against Me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>then I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3549AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3549AL\"></sup>act with hostility against you; and I, even I, will strike you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3549AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3549AM\"></sup>seven times for your sins.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I will also bring upon you a sword which will execute <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3550AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3550AN\"></sup>vengeance for the covenant; and when you gather together into your cities, I will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3550AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3550AO\"></sup>pestilence among you, so that you shall be delivered into enemy hands.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3551AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3551AP\"></sup>When I break your staff of bread, ten women will bake your bread in one oven, and they will bring back your bread in rationed amounts, so that you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3551AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3551AQ\"></sup>eat and not be satisfied.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘Yet if in spite of this you do not obey Me, but act with hostility against Me,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3553AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3553AR\"></sup>I will act with wrathful hostility against you, and I, even I, will punish you seven times for your sins.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Further, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3554AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3554AS\"></sup>you will eat the flesh of your sons and the flesh of your daughters you will eat.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3555AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3555AT\"></sup>will destroy your high places, and cut down your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3555AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3555AU\"></sup>incense altars, and heap your remains on the remains of your idols, for My soul shall abhor you.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I will lay <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3556AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3556AV\"></sup>waste your cities as well and will make your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3556AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3556AW\"></sup>sanctuaries desolate, and I will not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3556AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3556AX\"></sup>smell your soothing aromas.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>I will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3557AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3557AY\"></sup>the land desolate <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3557AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3557AZ\"></sup>so that your enemies who settle in it will be appalled over it.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>You, however, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3558BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3558BA\"></sup>will scatter among the nations and will draw out a sword after you, as your land becomes desolate and your cities become waste.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3559BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3559BB\"></sup>Then the land will enjoy its sabbaths all the days of the desolation, while you are in your enemies’ land; then the land will rest and enjoy its sabbaths.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All the days of <i>its</i> desolation it will observe the rest which it did not observe on your sabbaths, while you were living on it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As for those of you who may be left, I will also bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3561BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3561BC\"></sup>weakness into their hearts in the lands of their enemies. And the sound of a driven leaf will chase them, and even when no one is pursuing they will flee as though from the sword, and they will fall.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3562BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3562BD\"></sup>They will therefore stumble over each other as if <i>running</i> from the sword, although no one is pursuing; and you will have <i>no strength</i> to stand up before your enemies.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3563BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3563BE\"></sup>you will perish among the nations, and your enemies’ land will consume you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3564BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3564BF\"></sup>So those of you who may be left will rot away because of their iniquity in the lands of your enemies; and also because of the iniquities of their forefathers they will rot away with them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3565BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3565BG\"></sup>If they confess their iniquity and the iniquity of their forefathers, in their unfaithfulness which they committed against Me, and also in their acting with hostility against Me—",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>I also was acting with hostility against them, to bring them into the land of their enemies—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3566BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3566BH\"></sup>or if their uncircumcised heart becomes humbled so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3566BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3566BI\"></sup>they then make amends for their iniquity,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>then I will remember <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3567BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3567BJ\"></sup>My covenant with Jacob, and I will remember also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3567BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3567BK\"></sup>My covenant with Isaac, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3567BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3567BL\"></sup>My covenant with Abraham as well, and I will remember the land.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3568BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3568BM\"></sup>For the land will be abandoned by them, and will make up for its sabbaths while it is made desolate without them. They, meanwhile, will be making amends for their iniquity, because they rejected My ordinances and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3568BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3568BN\"></sup>soul abhorred My statutes.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Yet in spite of this, when they are in the land of their enemies, I will not reject them, nor will I so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3569BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3569BO\"></sup>abhor them as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3569BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3569BP\"></sup>to destroy them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3569BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3569BQ\"></sup>breaking My covenant with them; for I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But I will remember for them the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3570BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3570BR\"></sup>covenant with their ancestors, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt in the sight of the nations, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3570BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3570BS\"></sup>I might be their God. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3571BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3571BT\"></sup>These are the statutes and ordinances and laws which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> established between Himself and the sons of Israel through Moses at Mount Sinai."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Again, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the sons of Israel and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3573A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3573A\"></sup>When a man makes a difficult vow, he <i>shall be valued</i> according to your valuation of persons belonging to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If your valuation is of the male from twenty years even to sixty years old, then your valuation shall be fifty shekels of silver, after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3574B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3574B\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Or if it is a female, then your valuation shall be thirty shekels.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If it be from five years even to twenty years old then your valuation for the male shall be twenty shekels and for the female ten shekels.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if <i>they are</i> from a month even up to five years old, then your valuation shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3577C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3577C\"></sup>five shekels of silver for the male, and for the female your valuation shall be three shekels of silver.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If <i>they are</i> from sixty years old and upward, if it is a male, then your valuation shall be fifteen shekels, and for the female ten shekels.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if he is poorer than your valuation, then he shall be placed before the priest and the priest shall value him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3579D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3579D\"></sup>according to the means of the one who vowed, the priest shall value him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘Now if it is an animal of the kind which men can present as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, any such that one gives to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be holy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3581E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3581E\"></sup>He shall not replace it or exchange it, a good for a bad, or a bad for a good; or if he does exchange animal for animal, then both it and its substitute shall become holy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If, however, it is any unclean animal of the kind which men do not present as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then he shall place the animal before the priest.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The priest shall value it as either good or bad; as you, the priest, value it, so it shall be.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if he should ever <i>wish to</i> redeem it, then he shall add one-fifth of it to your valuation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘Now if a man consecrates his house as holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then the priest shall value it as either good or bad; as the priest values it, so it shall stand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Yet if the one who consecrates it should <i>wish to</i> redeem his house, then he shall add one-fifth of your valuation price to it, so that it may be his.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>‘Again, if a man consecrates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> part of the fields of his own property, then your valuation shall be proportionate to the seed needed for it: a homer of barley seed at fifty shekels of silver.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If he consecrates his field as of the year of jubilee, according to your valuation it shall stand.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If he consecrates his field after the jubilee, however, then the priest shall calculate the price for him proportionate to the years that are left until the year of jubilee; and it shall be deducted from your valuation.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If the one who consecrates it should ever wish to redeem the field, then he shall add one-fifth of your valuation price to it, so that it may pass to him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Yet if he will not redeem the field, but has sold the field to another man, it may no longer be redeemed;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and when it reverts in the jubilee, the field shall be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, like a field set apart; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3592F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3592F\"></sup>it shall be for the priest as his property.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Or if he consecrates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a field which he has bought, which is not a part of the field of his own property,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then the priest shall calculate for him the amount of your valuation up to the year of jubilee; and he shall on that day give your valuation as holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In the year of jubilee the field shall return to the one from whom he bought it, to whom the possession of the land belongs.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Every valuation of yours, moreover, shall be after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3596G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3596G\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary. The shekel shall be twenty gerahs.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3597H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3597H\"></sup>However, a firstborn among animals, which as a firstborn belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, no man may consecrate it; whether ox or sheep, it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But if <i>it is</i> among the unclean animals, then he shall redeem it according to your valuation and add to it one-fifth of it; and if it is not redeemed, then it shall be sold according to your valuation.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>‘Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3599I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3599I\"></sup>anything which a man sets apart to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of all that he has, of man or animal or of the fields of his own property, shall not be sold or redeemed. Anything devoted to destruction is most holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>No one who may have been set apart among men shall be ransomed; he shall surely be put to death.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>‘Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3601J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3601J\"></sup>all the tithe of the land, of the seed of the land or of the fruit of the tree, is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span>; it is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If, therefore, a man wishes to redeem part of his tithe, he shall add to it one-fifth of it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For every tenth part of herd or flock, whatever <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3603K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3603K\"></sup>passes under the rod, the tenth one shall be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3604L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3604L\"></sup>He is not to be concerned whether <i>it is</i> good or bad, nor shall he exchange it; or if he does exchange it, then both it and its substitute shall become holy. It shall not be redeemed.’”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3605M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3605M\"></sup>These are the commandments which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses for the sons of Israel at Mount Sinai."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;